#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:726-5
msgctxt "user_guide/en.html+html.body.div.div:726-5"
msgid "USER INTERFACE"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:728-5
msgid ""
"KOReader has a simple, mainly black and white user interface because "
"gradients and different shades of gray can cause flashing and ghosting on e-"
"ink screens which can degrade reading experience."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:730-5
msgid ""
"KOReader has 2 main interfaces: <span class=\"ui\">READING SCREEN</span> and "
"<span class=\"ui\">FILE BROWSER</span>."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:733-5
msgctxt "user_guide/en.html+html.body.div.div:733-5"
msgid "Reading Screen"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:735-5
msgid ""
"<b>READING SCREEN</b> has two toolbars. <span class=\"ui\">TOP MENU</span> "
"includes menu items related to the general usage of KOReader. You will "
"access your books, KOReader preferences, plugins etc. here. <span class="
"\"ui\">BOTTOM MENU</span> is focused on options for document formatting like "
"font weight/size, line spacing etc. While adjusting your text appearance, "
"you will mostly interact with the <span class=\"ui\">BOTTOM MENU</span>."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:745-5
msgid ""
"On the right you can see the default tap zones of KOReader. To show the "
"<span class=\"ui\">TOP MENU</span> or <span class=\"ui\">BOTTOM MENU</span> "
"you can tap the indicated zones. You can also swipe down the upper zone to "
"show the <span class=\"ui\">TOP MENU</span>. On non-touch devices like "
"Kindle 4 you can open the <span class=\"ui\">BOTTOM MENU</span> by pressing "
"the button that corresponds to the <b>ENTER/OK</b> action."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:747-5
msgid ""
"You can set <span class=\"ui\">TOP MENU</span> zone to open both the <span "
"class=\"ui\">TOP</span> and <span class=\"ui\">BOTTOM MENU</span> at the "
"same time via this menu:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:749-5
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/gear.svg\" style="
"\"width:26px;\"> → Taps and Gestures → Activate Menu"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:753-5
msgid ""
"<span class=\"ui\">CORNER TAP ZONES</span> can be used for many different "
"type of gestures including <b>TAP, DOUBLE TAP, TWO FINGER TAP</b> and <b>TAP "
"and HOLD</b>."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:754-5
msgid ""
"<b>PREVIOUS PAGE</b> and <b>NEXT PAGE</b> zones can also be used for "
"<b>DOUBLE TAP</b> gestures at the same time."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:755-5
msgid ""
"<span class=\"ui\">STATUS BAR</span> zone can be tapped to cycle between "
"<span class=\"ui\">STATUS BAR</span> items if only one item is visible. If "
"all items are visible, tapping will show and hide the <span class=\"ui\""
">STATUS BAR</span>. Check <b>“How can I configure the status bar ?”</b> "
"heading for more info."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:758-5
msgctxt "user_guide/en.html+html.body.div.div:758-5"
msgid "File Browser"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:760-5
msgid ""
"You will see <span class=\"ui\">FILE BROWSER</span> when you run KOReader "
"for the first time. You can access it from the reading screen by:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:762-5
msgid "⇑ TOP MENU →"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:768-5
msgid ""
"By default, <span class=\"ui\">FILE BROWSER</span> shows your <span class="
"\"ui\">HOME</span> which is your main library folder which you can change by "
"<b>tapping and holding on any folder</b>. You can change its many options "
"like how books are displayed or sorted via the <span class=\"ui\">TOP MENU</"
"span> by swiping down from the top part of the screen."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:769-5
msgid "Circled items in the image are explained below:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:770-5
msgid ""
"<span class=\"ui\">RESET:</span> This option allows you to reset some "
"properties of your document like <b>reading progress, bookmarks, custom "
"cover image</b> etc. which you can choose in a following dialog."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:771-5
msgid ""
"<span class=\"label_red\">WARNING</span> Be very careful when using this "
"dialog and double check which items are marked, otherwise you can reset "
"everything accidentally."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:772-5
msgid ""
"<span class=\"ui\">OPEN WITH:</span> KOReader has different engines for "
"rendering different file types. In some cases you can open a file in a "
"different engine to get some other features. See <b>Viewing archive files</"
"b> and <b>Viewing image files</b> sections just below."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:773-5
msgid ""
"<span class=\"ui\">IGNORE COVER:</span> If for some reason you want to "
"disable the cover for this book (it may have wrong cover or cover is not "
"very readable on the e-ink screen) you can select this."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:774-5
msgid ""
"<span class=\"ui\">IGNORE METADATA:</span> If your book metadata is not "
"correct, name field may show useless information. Select this option to show "
"the file name instead of metadata."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:775-5
msgid ""
"<span class=\"ui\">REFRESH CACHED BOOK INFORMATION:</span> KOReader caches a "
"book's metadata and book cover when you add it to your library. If you make "
"some changes to the book after copying to your device, this information "
"might need to be updated. If you see wrong cover or metadata, you can "
"refresh the book information with this menu item."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:778-5
msgid "Viewing archive files"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:779-5
msgid ""
"You can open <b>ZIP</b>, <b>CBZ</b> and <b>EPUB</b> (as they are <b>ZIP</b> "
"archives too) files with the archive viewer to have a look at the contained "
"files:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ol.li:784-5
msgctxt "user_guide/en.html+html.body.div.div.ol.li:784-5"
msgid "In <span class=\"ui\">File Browser</span> long-press the file name"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ol.li:785-5
msgctxt "user_guide/en.html+html.body.div.div.ol.li:785-5"
msgid "Tap <span class=\"ui\">Open with…</span>"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ol.li:786-5
msgid "Tap <span class=\"ui\">Archive viewer</span>"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:790-5
msgid "Viewing image files"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:791-5
msgid ""
"You can open image files with the image viewer instead of opening as a book. "
"Files opened like this don’t show up in your history and have better scaling "
"and rotation support."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ol.li:793-5
msgctxt "user_guide/en.html+html.body.div.div.ol.li:793-5"
msgid "In <span class=\"ui\">File Browser</span> long-press the file name"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ol.li:794-5
msgctxt "user_guide/en.html+html.body.div.div.ol.li:794-5"
msgid "Tap <span class=\"ui\">Open with…</span>"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ol.li:795-5
msgid "Tap <span class=\"ui\">Image viewer</span>"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:799-5
msgid "Setting file associations"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:800-5
msgid ""
"You can also set file associations for file types which KOReader doesn’t "
"automatically recognize. To associate a file with one of the KOReader "
"providers, first long tap on your file in the <span class=\"ui\">File "
"Browser</span> then choose a provider engine to handle this file. You can "
"check:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:803-9
msgid ""
"<span class=\"ui\">Always use this engine for this file</span> to associate "
"this provider with this particular file only"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:804-9
msgid ""
"Or check <span class=\"ui\">Always use this engine for file type</span> to "
"associate this provider with all the files that has same extension as this "
"one From the same dialog, you can see the associations you made by tapping "
"on <span class=\"ui\">View defaults for file types</span>."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:813-5
msgid "Accessing your books"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:814-5
msgid "Following methods are available for accessing your books and articles:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:817-5
msgid "<span class=\"ui\">File Browser</span> - As explained above"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:818-5
msgid ""
"<span class=\"ui\">Favorites</span> - A list which you can add your books by "
"long pressing on them in the <span class=\"ui\">File Browser</span>"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:819-5
msgid "<span class=\"ui\">History</span> - List of books you opened"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:822-5
msgid "You can change how these screens look from:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:824-5
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU (in File Browser) → <img class=\"img_inline\" src="
"\"pictures/top_cabinet.svg\" style=\"width:26px;\"> → Display mode"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:826-5
msgid ""
"If you want to change how many items are visible on these screens, look here:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:828-5
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU (in File Browser) → <img class=\"img_inline\" src="
"\"pictures/top_cabinet.svg\" style=\"width:26px;\"> → Settings → Mosaic and "
"detailed list settings"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:830-5
msgid ""
"You can assign gestures for each of these dialogs. For example while reading "
"a book, you can access your <span class=\"ui\">History</span> or <span class="
"\"ui\">Favorites</span> with a gesture and open another book without going "
"through the <span class=\"ui\">File Browser</span>."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:831-5
msgid ""
"You can search a book in the <span class=\"ui\">History</span> screen by "
"<b>filename</b> or <b>book metadata</b> from the upper left hamburger menu "
"button."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:832-5
msgid ""
"You can also set KOReader to start with <span class=\"ui\">Favorites</span> "
"or <span class=\"ui\">History</span> screen instead of <span class=\"ui\""
">File Browser</span> via:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:835-5
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU (in File Browser) → <img class=\"img_inline\" src="
"\"pictures/top_cabinet.svg\" style=\"width:26px;\"> → Start with"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:840-5
msgctxt "user_guide/en.html+html.body.div.div:840-5"
msgid "Folder shortcuts"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:841-5
msgid ""
"KOReader allows you to add your favorite folders to a quickly accessible "
"Folder shortcuts menu. For example if you have an <b>Archive</b> folder in "
"your library that is under <b>Home>Articles>Scientific>Archived</b>, you can "
"assign a folder shortcut to this <b>Archived</b> folder and access it "
"quickly even while reading a book."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:844-5
msgid "Adding a folder shortcut"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:845-5
msgid ""
"There are two ways of adding a folder to your <span class=\"ui\">Folder "
"shortcuts</span> list:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ol.li:847-9
msgid ""
"When you are in the File Browser, tap right corner <span class=\"ui\">+ "
"(plus) menu</span> button then tap <span class=\"ui\">Add to folder "
"shortcuts</span> item and enter a descriptive name for this shortcut. "
"<b>This will add the folder you are currently in.</b>"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ol.li:848-9
msgid ""
"When you are in the File Browser, long-press on a folder name to open the "
"context menu. Tap <span class=\"ui\">Add to folder shortcuts</span> item and "
"enter a descriptive name for this shortcut. <b>This will add the folder you "
"pressed on.</b>"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:851-5
msgid ""
"Folders which are in your <span class=\"ui\">Folder shortcuts</span> list "
"will have a <b>star (★)</b> in the <span class=\"ui\">File Browser</span>."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:853-5
msgid ""
"You can remove a folder from the shortcuts in the same way, by long-pressing "
"on it and selecting <span class=\"ui\">Remove from folder shortcuts</span>."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:856-5
msgid "Viewing your folder shortcuts"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:857-5
msgid ""
"You can open your <span class=\"ui\">Folder shortcuts</span> from the <span "
"class=\"ui\">File Browser</span> or <span class=\"ui\">Reading screen</span> "
"while reading a book."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:859-9
msgid ""
"<b>From the File browser:</b> Top right corner <span class=\"ui\">+ (plus) "
"menu</span> then choosing <span class=\"ui\">Folder shortcuts</span> or "
"assigning a gesture."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:860-9
msgid "<b>From the reading screen:</b> By assigning a gesture to it."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:863-5
msgid ""
"It is under the <span class=\"ui\">File browser</span> section of the <span "
"class=\"ui\">Gesture manager</span>. You can learn how to set gestures in "
"the relevant section of this guide."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:867-5
msgctxt "user_guide/en.html+html.body.div.div:867-5"
msgid "User Interface Tips"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:870-5
msgid ""
"<span class=\"label_blue\">INFO</span> KOReader’s user interface and options "
"can change depending on the file type you open. There are two categories: "
"<b>Fixed layout documents</b> (PDF, DJVU, image files...) and <b>Reflowable "
"documents</b> (EPUB, HTML, DOCX, RTF, TXT…)."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:874-9
msgid "You can change the interface language via:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li.div:874-56
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/gear.svg\" style="
"\"width:26px;\"> → Language"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:876-9
msgid ""
"If you tap and hold an <b>option</b> or <b>menu item</b> (font weight, line "
"spacing etc.), you can set its value as <span class=\"ui\">DEFAULT</span>. "
"The new value will only be applied to books opened from now on. Previously "
"opened books will keep their settings. You can identify default values as a "
"<span class=\"ui\">star</span> (★) in the menu or as a <span class=\"ui\""
">black border</span> around the indicators as seen below:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:881-9
msgid ""
"On the <b>BOTTOM MENU</b> if you tap and hold an option’s name, you can see "
"its explanation."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:883-9
msgid ""
"You can <b>CLOSE</b> full screen dialogs (<span class=\"ui\">History, Table "
"of Contents, Bookmarks, Reading Statistics</span> etc.) by <b>swiping "
"down.</b>"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:885-9
msgid ""
"You can take a screenshot by making a <b>long diagonal swipe</b> with your "
"finger. Also <b>touching opposing diagonal corners</b> will take a "
"screenshot. You can use this second shortcut for example when viewing an "
"image."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li.p:888-9
msgid ""
"In dialogs containing adjustment arrow buttons like the one above, you can "
"<b>tap and hold</b> on arrow buttons to change the value in bigger "
"increments."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li.p:889-9
msgid ""
"You can <b>CLOSE</b> this type of dialog (non-full screen) by tapping "
"outside of its window."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li.p:890-9
msgid ""
"You can <b>MOVE</b> this type of dialog by holding its window title and "
"dragging."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li.p:891-9
msgid ""
"You can make this type of dialog <b>SEMI-TRANSPARENT</b> by tapping and "
"holding the <b>window title</b> (when you want to see the text under it "
"while adjusting a value)."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:894-9
msgid ""
"KOReader supports <b>dictionary lookup</b> in EPUB and scanned PDF/DJVU "
"documents. To see the dictionary definition or translation, just tap and "
"hold a word."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:896-9
msgid ""
"Pressing and holding a word brings up a dialog where you can also search the "
"selection in the document for more occurrences or look it up on Wikipedia."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:898-9
msgid ""
"If you want to change the size of user interface, there is a <span class="
"\"ui\">DPI</span> setting for that:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li.div:900-9
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/gear.svg\" style="
"\"width:26px;\"> → Screen → Screen DPI"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li.p:902-9
msgid ""
"You can choose a value from the menu or select <span class=\"ui\">CUSTOM "
"DPI</span> to enter a value for fine tuning: <b>Higher DPI = Bigger "
"Interface</b>"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li.p:903-9
msgid ""
"Note that there is also a <span class=\"ui\">Zoom (dpi)</span> setting in "
"the bottom bar. That one is related to the documents only. You can find the "
"explanation in the next section."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:906-9
msgid ""
"You can disable black flashing (automatic partial refresh to clear ghosting) "
"of user interface if it disturbs you:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li.div:907-9
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/gear.svg\" style="
"\"width:26px;\"> → Screen → E-ink Settings"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:910-9
msgid ""
"If you want to check the current date you can tap on the clock in the <span "
"class=\"ui\">TOP MENU</span>."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:915-5
msgctxt "user_guide/en.html+html.body.div.div:915-5"
msgid "Menu search"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:917-5
msgid ""
"KOReader has lots of features so its menu system reflects this complexity. "
"We have a Menu Search feature for finding menu items quickly. You can access "
"it from:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:921-5
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/top_hamburger.svg\" "
"style=\"width:26px;\"> → Help → Menu search"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:923-5
msgid ""
"Also you can assign this feature to a gesture or add it to your <span class="
"\"ui\">Quick Menu</span> for faster access."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:926-5
msgid "Scrolling types"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:928-5
msgid "KOReader has three types of touch scrolling. You can access this from:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:930-5
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/gear.svg\" style="
"\"width:26px;\"> → Taps and Gestures → Scrolling"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:932-5
msgid ""
"<span class=\"label_blue\">INFO</span> You have to enable <span class=\"ui\""
">Continuous mode</span> from the <span class=\"ui\">Bottom menu</span> to be "
"able to use scrolling."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:934-5
msgid ""
"<b>Classic scrolling:</b> This mode works exactly like your phone/tablet "
"scrolling."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:936-5
msgid ""
"<b>Turbo scrolling:</b> This mode allows you to scroll faster than <span "
"class=\"ui\">classic scrolling</span>. Also you can scroll several pages "
"without lifting your finger. Scrolling amount is proportional to the "
"distance you move your finger after you initiated scrolling."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:938-5
msgid ""
"<b>On-release scrolling:</b> This scrolling type is more suitable for e-ink "
"screens. Because unlike other scrolling types, this mode doesn’t refresh "
"your page continuously while scrolling. It works like <span class=\"ui\""
">classic scrolling</span> but intermediate steps are not shown. So you "
"scroll with your finger and when you release, page jumps to that position. "
"This is especially useful <b>to reposition and adjust the view</b> if your "
"book contains pictures or tables and you want to see all of it."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:941-5
msgid "Go back to previous location"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:942-5
msgid ""
"This useful feature works like the <b>Back</b> button in your browser. When "
"you jump to some other part of the book using <span class=\"ui\">Skim "
"widget, Bookmarks list, Book map</span> etc. KOReader remembers your "
"previous location. This is useful for example if you follow an internal link "
"or reference. With one tap you can go back to where you come from. You can "
"access this feature from:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:946-5
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/top_bookmark.svg\" "
"style=\"width:26px;\"> → Go back to previous location"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:948-5
msgid ""
"Also you can go forward too, from the same menu. This feature is assigned to "
"← → multiswipe gesture. You can assign this to another gesture if you want ("
"like tapping a corner) or add it to your <span class=\"ui\">Quick "
"Menu</span>."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:952-5
msgid "Prevent flashing on pages with images"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:954-5
msgid ""
"KOReader normally perform a full refresh on pages containing images (which "
"you can observe as a black flash). The reason is to get rid of the residue "
"and ghosting from the previous page. But this might not be necessary "
"depending on your device and personal preferences. You can disable this auto-"
"refresh behavior here:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:958-5
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/gear.svg\" style="
"\"width:24px;\"> → Screen → E-ink Settings → Full refresh rate → Always "
"flash on pages with images"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:960-5
msgid "Partial rendering support"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:962-5
msgid ""
"With the version 2023.03, KOReader gained partial rendering capability while "
"reading EPUB documents. Before this version, when you made an adjustment "
"like changing font size, the whole book had to be rendered again to be able "
"to preview the new setting. Depending on the device and book size, this can "
"take a while to calculate."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:965-5
msgid ""
"With this new feature, when reading EPUB documents, text appearance "
"adjustments can be done much quicker by only rendering the current chapter."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:967-5
msgid ""
"<span class=\"label_blue\">INFO</span> This is only possible if your EPUB is "
"composed of multiple fragments. EPUB files are basically .zip archives that "
"contain .html files. Some books can be a single .html file while others may "
"be composed of multiple .html files like each chapter of the book is a "
"separate .html file. <b>If your book is only a single .html file, partial "
"rendering can not work, because for each change KOReader still has to "
"calculate the whole book.</b>"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:970-5
msgid ""
"Also rotating your screen orientation is now much faster thanks to this "
"feature. This feature is <b>ENABLED</b> by default. If necessary, it can be "
"disabled per book (with a tap), or globally (with a long-tap) on:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:974-5
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/gear.svg\" style="
"\"width:24px;\"> → Document → Enable partial renderings"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:976-5
msgid ""
"After these partial renderings, KOReader and the book enter a degraded state:"
" You can turn pages but some info and features may be broken or disabled ("
"i.e. footer info, ToC, statistics…). To get back to a normal working state, "
"KOReader has to render the rest of the book too. While this is happening, an "
"icon at the top left corner of the screen indicates the status:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ol.li:982-9
msgid ""
"Document is <b>partially</b> rendered. Page count, footer info and many "
"things are <b>innacurate</b>. You can see how the new settings look and "
"adjust further. You can also turn pages, jump links in this state."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ol.li:985-9
msgid ""
"A full rendering is happening in the <b>background</b>. You can still turn "
"pages, jump links, change settings."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ol.li:988-9
msgid ""
"Full rendering is done, but <b>not yet applied</b> because KOReader is "
"waiting for you to be <b>idle</b> to reload the rest of the book (idle=not "
"interacting with the device). You can still turn pages, jump links, change "
"settings."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ol.li:991-9
msgid ""
"You've been idle for a while so KOReader is now reloading the whole "
"document. At this step KOReader is <b>blocked</b> to prevent interaction."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:998-5
msgid ""
"When these icons are all gone, you are again in a fully working state. "
"Generally this whole process is quick and as a user you don’t need to do "
"anything extra. You can just adjust your settings and continue reading your "
"book, KOReader will do the rest."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1002-5
msgctxt "user_guide/en.html+html.body.div.div:1002-5"
msgid "Bottom Menu Items Explained"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1004-5
msgid ""
"<span class=\"label_green\">TIP</span> You can see an explanation of these "
"items when you long tap on their names in the bottom menu."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1009-5
msgid ""
"<span class=\"ui\">VIEW MODE:</span> If you change to <span class=\"ui\""
">CONTINUOUS</span> mode you can scroll the document like a web page. This "
"mode is more suitable for non e-ink screen types (LCD, OLED). In continuous "
"mode <b>you lose TOP and BOTTOM MARGINS</b> so text may be cut on first and "
"last line of screen. To solve this problem you can enable <span class=\"ui\""
">PAGE OVERLAP</span>:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1013-5
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/top_document.svg\" "
"style=\"width:26px;\"> → Page Overlap"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1015-5
msgid ""
"<span class=\"ui\">RENDER MODE:</span> This option determines how your "
"document is rendered by KOReader. Default is <span class=\"ui\">WEB</span> "
"and generally you don’t need to change this setting. When a book (or saved "
"web page) is very complicated (specified widths or margins, negative "
"margins, floats etc.) and layout looks bad or overflow the screen, you can "
"try other rendering modes."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1018-5
msgid ""
"<span class=\"ui\">ZOOM (dpi):</span> This setting can be thought of as a "
"<b>general zoom factor</b> for the document (except font size). At 96 dpi ("
"which is the default setting), images in the document are rendered at their "
"original dimensions. Basically you will use this setting if you want to "
"<b>make images bigger without making the text bigger</b>."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1025-5
msgid ""
"<span class=\"ui\">WORD SPACING and WORD EXPANSION:</span> These two "
"settings are related and they determine how your text will look when it is "
"justified. When you justify text, space is added between words so that both "
"edges of each line are aligned with both margins. Since word counts of lines "
"are not equal all the time, in justified alignment, text has to be "
"compressed or expanded to fill the line."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1027-5
msgid ""
"<span class=\"ui\">WORD SPACING:</span> How much the <b>SPACE</b> characters "
"in a line of text can be compressed to fit more words. This setting doesn’t "
"affect words, it only changes the space between them."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1028-5
msgid ""
"<span class=\"ui\">WORD EXPANSION:</span> If you have too much white space "
"in a line, how much of that can be distributed into the words by expanding "
"them. This setting affects the appearance of words. If you don’t want your "
"words to expand, set this to <span class=\"ui\">NONE</span>."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1031-5
msgid ""
"You can experiment with different settings until the text looks pleasing to "
"you, then set them as defaults via their respective dialogs."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1038-5
msgid ""
"<span class=\"ui\">CONTRAST</span> and <span class=\"ui\">FONT WEIGHT</span> "
"are two options that you can use to make your text bolder (or lighter). You "
"can achieve the same appearance with either of these options but they use "
"different methods to achieve it. Of course you can use them both at the same "
"time. The differences between them can be summarized as:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div.div:1045-9
msgid "CONTRAST"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div.div.p:1047-13
msgid "<b>+</b> Doesn’t change font width, book length stays the same"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div.div.p:1048-13
msgid "<b>+</b> Doesn’t need to re-render document, faster"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div.div.p:1049-13
msgid "<b>-</b> Might look bad on LCD or low DPI screens"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div.div:1051-9
msgid "FONT WEIGHT"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div.div.p:1053-13
msgid "<b>+</b> Will use proper weighted fonts if you have them installed"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div.div.p:1054-13
msgid "<b>+</b> Looks better on LCD or low DPI screens"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div.div.p:1055-13
msgid "<b>-</b> Has to re-render fonts, slower"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1060-5
msgid ""
"<span class=\"ui\">FONT HINTING</span> adjusts your text for maximum "
"readability according to your screen’s pixel grid. <span class=\"ui\""
">NATIVE</span> uses font’s internal hinting instructions, <span class=\"ui\""
">AUTO</span> uses FreeType’s hinting algorithm. <span class=\"ui\">AUTO</"
"span> is a safer choice because font files that you installed may have "
"problematic hinting instructions. Also <span class=\"ui\">AUTO</span> "
"handles <b>CJK</b> text better. You can try different settings to see which "
"one looks better on your device."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1062-5
msgid ""
"<span class=\"ui\">FONT KERNING</span> adjusts the spacing between letters "
"to achieve a visually pleasing result. Default is <span class=\"ui\">BEST</"
"span>, which might be <b>slower</b> when opening files (depending on your "
"device) but <b>has better support for ligatures</b> (see picture below for "
"an example), joined <b>Arabic</b> glyphs and some other scripts. If your "
"device is slow, you can try <span class=\"ui\">GOOD</span> which is faster "
"and may still look correct with western latin-script text."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1071-5
msgid ""
"<span class=\"ui\">ALT STATUS BAR</span> enables an alternative status bar "
"which is available only in reflowable documents (EPUB, HTML, DOCX, RTF, TXT…)"
". After enabling it here, you can configure <span class=\"ui\">ALT STATUS "
"BAR</span> via:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1075-5
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/gear.svg\" style="
"\"width:26px;\"> → Status Bar → Alt status bar"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1077-5
msgid ""
"<span class=\"ui\">EMBEDDED STYLE</span> and <span class=\"ui\">EMBEDDED "
"FONTS</span> determine if publisher’s styles and fonts embedded in the "
"document will be used (or ignored) to render the document. These are general "
"on/off switches. You can achieve more fine tuned tweaks for your document "
"via:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1081-5
msgctxt "user_guide/en.html+html.body.div.div:1081-5"
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/top_document.svg\" "
"style=\"width:26px;\"> → Style Tweaks"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1083-5
msgid ""
"<span class=\"ui\">IMAGE SCALING</span> determines how images in your "
"document are rendered. <span class=\"ui\">BEST</span> looks more pleasing "
"but it is slower."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1089-5
msgid "Saving your text appearance settings for later use"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1090-5
msgid ""
"This powerful feature allows you to save all the <span class=\"ui\">BOTTOM "
"MENU</span> settings + font type as a <b>profile</b>. This means you can "
"have different group of settings for different conditions or book types "
"which you can apply at once instead of changing the settings manually every "
"time. For example you can create a:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:1094-9
msgid ""
"<b>Double column</b> profile with <span class=\"ui\">two columns</span> of "
"small sized text, <span class=\"ui\">landscape orientation</span> and "
"minimum <span class=\"ui\">margins</span>"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:1095-9
msgid ""
"<b>Night reading</b> profile with <span class=\"ui\">bigger sans serif font</"
"span> and higher <span class=\"ui\">contrast</span> for more visible text "
"under low light"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:1096-9
msgid ""
"<b>Disabled styles</b> profile with <span class=\"ui\">embedded style</span> "
"and <span class=\"ui\">embedded fonts</span> disabled for badly structured "
"books"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul:1096-162
msgid ""
"After adjusting your settings to your liking, you can create a profile from "
"them via:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1101-5
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/top_tools.svg\" style="
"\"width:26px;\"> → Profiles → New with current document settings"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1103-5
msgid ""
"After creating a profile with your settings, you have many options for "
