msgid ""
"KOReader can show chapter boundaries from your documents on the <span class="
"\"ui\">SKIM WIDGET</span> and <span class=\"ui\">PROGRESS BAR</span>."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1424-5
msgid ""
"If your document has too many heading levels, your chapter marks can look "
"crowded like the example above. You can change the depth of visible ToC mark "
"levels via:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:1426-5
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/top_bookmark.svg\" "
"style=\"width:26px;\"> → Settings → Progress Bars"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1430-5
msgid "You can also use this reduced ToC for:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:1432-9
msgid "chapter titles (if it is shown on <span class=\"ui\">Status Bar</span>)"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:1433-9
msgid "chapter navigation"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:1434-9
msgid "reading time left estimates"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1436-5
msgid "These options are in the same menu."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1437-5
msgid ""
"If your document doesn’t have a Table of Contents, you can enable <span "
"class=\"ui\">ALTERNATIVE TABLE OF CONTENTS</span>. When this setting is "
"enabled, KOReader will build a ToC from document headings (if available) or "
"from individual HTML files in the EPUB. Long press on this menu item for "
"extra info:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:1440-5
msgctxt "user_guide/en.html+html.body.div.div.div:1440-5"
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/top_bookmark.svg\" "
"style=\"width:26px;\"> → Settings → Alternative table of contents"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1442-5
msgid ""
"You can find more info about the <b>table of contents</b> tools available in "
"KOReader in this relevant section of the guide: <a href=\"#toctools\">TABLE "
"OF CONTENTS TOOLS</a>"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1446-5
msgctxt "user_guide/en.html+html.body.div.div:1446-5"
msgid "Book Map"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1448-5
msgid ""
"Book map is a powerful and unique feature of KOReader which can be very "
"useful for getting an overview of a book. For example if you are reading a "
"book non-linearly by skipping some parts to read them later, it would be "
"hard to track your progress. Book Map can show you which parts of the book "
"you have already read, at a glance."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1450-5
msgid "Additionally you can:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:1452-9
msgid ""
"See how much time you have spent on each page (if <span class=\"ui\">Reading "
"Statistics</span> plugin is enabled)"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:1453-9
msgid "Check which pages have bookmark, highlights and notes"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:1454-9
msgid ""
"Navigate directly to any part of the book like the <span class=\"ui\">SKIM "
"WIDGET</span>"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul:1454-97
msgid ""
"You can access Book Map via menu and you can also assign a gesture for "
"quicker access:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:1459-5
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/top_bookmark.svg\" "
"style=\"width:26px;\"> → Book map"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1464-5
msgid "User Interface And Controls"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1465-5
msgid ""
"When you open the <span class=\"ui\">Book Map</span> first time while "
"reading a book, it will be in <span class=\"ui\">Grid View</span> mode, "
"fitting all chapters on a single screen to give the best initial overview of "
"the book’s content. To get a detailed information about usage, tap the info "
"icon at the upper left corner. You can close the Book Map by tapping <span "
"class=\"ui\">X</span> on the upper right corner or with any multiswipe "
"gesture (<b>UP-DOWN, LEFT-RIGHT</b> etc.)."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1470-5
msgid ""
"You can customize <span class=\"ui\">Book Map</span> by changing these "
"options:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1471-5
msgid ""
"- First try swiping <span class=\"ui\">LEFT</span> and <span class=\"ui\""
">RIGHT</span> along the bottom edge of the screen to change width of columns "
"indicating pages and observe how it changes the scale of map"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1473-5
msgid ""
"- Then try swiping <span class=\"ui\">UP</span> and <span class=\"ui\">DOWN</"
"span> along the left edge of the screen to change chapter title depth and "
"switch to the <span class=\"ui\">Flat View</span>. See examples below."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1475-5
msgid ""
"In addition to default <span class=\"ui\">Grid View</span> above, here you "
"can see the <span class=\"ui\">Flat View</span> on the left and Grid View "
"without chapter titles on the right. Note the changing left vertical "
"scrollbar between views. If you want to switch back to the default view, you "
"can long-press the info icon at the upper left corner."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1486-5
msgid "Book map options"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1490-5
msgid ""
"When you tap the menu icon on the <b>Book map</b> screen you are presented "
"with the menu above. Menu options are explained below:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:1493-9
msgid ""
"<span class=\"ui\">About book map:</span> Short explanation of Book map "
"usage and icon descriptions."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:1494-9
msgid ""
"<span class=\"ui\">Available gestures:</span> Gestures you can use to change "
"the settings of Book map instead of using this menu."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:1495-9
msgid ""
"<span class=\"ui\">Page browser on tap:</span> If this is checked, when you "
"tap on a page in Book map, <span class=\"ui\">Page browser</span> opens. "
"This shows you an overview of the area you selected. If you disable this "
"option, a tap in Book map directly takes you to that page. But remember, "
"depending on factors like your screen size, touch screen sensitivity, tap "
"accuracy etc. you might end up in adjacent pages."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:1496-9
msgid ""
"<span class=\"ui\">Switch current/initial views:</span> If you customized "
"your Book map view, tapping this switches between the <b>default view</b> "
"and your <b>customized view</b>."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:1497-9
msgid ""
"<span class=\"ui\">Switch grid/flat views:</span> Switch between separate "
"chapters or continuous chapters views."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:1498-9
msgid ""
"<span class=\"ui\">Chapter levels:</span> Change the depth of chapter/sub "
"chapter levels."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:1499-9
msgid ""
"<span class=\"ui\">Page slot width:</span> Make each page slot wider or "
"narrower."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:1500-9
msgid ""
"<span class=\"ui\">10-page markers:</span> As you increase this value, first "
"it will add markers to every <b>10<sup>th</sup> page</b>, then it will make "
"them bigger and eventually it will add markers to every <b>5<sup>th</sup> "
"page</b>."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1504-5
msgctxt "user_guide/en.html+html.body.div.div:1504-5"
msgid "Page Browser"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1505-5
msgid ""
"Page Browser can be used to navigate between pages like in a photo album by "
"showing thumbnails of the pages as a grid. You can open <span class=\"ui\""
">Page Browser</span> by tapping on the <span class=\"ui\">Book Map</span> or "
"from the menu. You can also assign a gesture for quick access."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:1508-5
msgctxt "user_guide/en.html+html.body.div.div.div:1508-5"
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/top_bookmark.svg\" "
"style=\"width:26px;\"> → Page browser"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1510-5
msgid ""
"You can change the number of pages shown by swiping along the <span class="
"\"ui\">TOP</span> and <span class=\"ui\">LEFT</span> sides of screen. Icons "
"on the bottom are the same as <span class=\"ui\">Book Map</span>. Actually "
"the bottom part is a linear version of the <span class=\"ui\">Book "
"Map</span>."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1516-5
msgid "Alternative theme for Book map and Page Browser"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1518-5
msgid ""
"Book map and page browser has an <b>Alternative theme</b> with a different "
"shading scheme which you can activate from their hamburger menus. This theme "
"uses alternating colors for the chapter headings so chapter boundaries is "
"more visible in the <span class=\"ui\">Book map</span> and <span class=\"ui\""
">Page browser</span>. But the usage of gray color in this theme requires "
"flashing to black so it might be distracting for some users. You can try "
"both and use the one you like."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1522-5
msgctxt "user_guide/en.html+html.body.div.div:1522-5"
msgid "Table of Contents Tools"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1523-5
msgid ""
"Some of the digital books you come across might not have a proper table of "
"contents (<b>ToC</b>). Depending on the preparation of the book, you can "
"experience these ToC problems:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:1526-9
msgid ""
"No ToC in the book, so you can’t jump between the chapters or see the "
"remaining reading times"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:1527-9
msgid ""
"There is a ToC but it is not very useful because it has wrong or missing "
"chapter titles"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1530-5
msgid ""
"KOReader has some features that you can use when reading books with a "
"problematic table of contents section."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1532-5
msgid ""
"Note that <span class=\"ui\">Alternative table of contents</span> is not "
"available on <b>fixed layout documents</b> like PDF, DJVU etc. because it "
"requires HTML tags to create a ToC. <span class=\"ui\">Custom table of "
"contents</span> and <span class=\"ui\">Custom hidden flows</span> features "
"are available on all file types."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1536-5
msgid ""
"Automatically creating a table of contents: ALTERNATIVE TABLE OF CONTENTS"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1538-5
msgid ""
"First feature is the <span class=\"ui\">Alternative table of contents</span> "
"which you can find in:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:1541-5
msgctxt "user_guide/en.html+html.body.div.div.div:1541-5"
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/top_bookmark.svg\" "
"style=\"width:26px;\"> → Settings → Alternative table of contents"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:1543-5
msgid ""
"<span class=\"label_blue\">INFO</span> An EPUB document is basically a ZIP "
"file containing one or more HTML files. Your book might be one big HTML file "
"for the whole book or it might contain separate chapters as individual HTML "
"files (which is a better structure)."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1545-5
msgid ""
"<span class=\"ui\">Alternative table of contents</span> tries to create a "
"ToC from the headings in your book (<b>H1</b> to <b>H6</b> tags in the HTML "
"files in your EPUB). If your book doesn’t contain any headings, it will try "
"to build a ToC from the document fragments (individual HTML files in your "
"EPUB book) which will point to the beginning of each file."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1547-5
msgid ""
"You can choose which heading levels to include (or ignore) in your ToC from "
"this menu:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:1549-5
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/top_document.svg\" "
"style=\"width:26px;\"> → Style tweaks → Miscellaneous → Alternative ToC hints"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1555-5
msgid "Manually creating a table of contents: CUSTOM TABLE OF CONTENTS"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1557-5
msgid ""
"Custom table of contents feature allows you to create your own ToC from the "
"selected parts of your book. This ToC can contain only one level so you can’"
"t have sub-chapters while using this feature. To create your own ToC, first "
"enable:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:1560-5
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/top_bookmark.svg\" "
"style=\"width:26px;\"> → Settings → Custom table of contents"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1562-5
msgid ""
"Once you enable this feature, new menu items will be added to the user "
"interface which allows you to select your chapters. You can add a chapter to "
"your ToC from two places:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ol.li:1565-9
msgid ""
"<b>From a highlight:</b> While reading a book, select a text like you are "
"highlighting it or long press on a word. In the popup menu you will see the "
"<span class=\"ui\">Start TOC chapter</span> item. When you press on it, you "
"will see a dialog asking you to enter your chapter title. The text you "
"selected will be already entered in the dialog. Edit your title if necessary "
"and press create."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ol.li:1566-9
msgid "<b>From the Page browser:</b> Open the Page browser via"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:1570-5
msgctxt "user_guide/en.html+html.body.div.div.div:1570-5"
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/top_bookmark.svg\" "
"style=\"width:26px;\"> → Page browser"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1572-5
msgid ""
"Long press on the page thumbnail that you want to be the beginning of your "
"chapter and select <span class=\"ui\">Start TOC chapter</span> item from the "
"popup menu. You will see a dialog asking you to enter your chapter title."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1574-5
msgid ""
"When you are done creating your ToC and don’t want to see these extra "
"buttons, you can disable them by unchecking:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:1576-5
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/top_bookmark.svg\" "
"style=\"width:26px;\"> → Settings → Custom layout features → Edit mode"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1578-5
msgid ""
"Creating this ToC will not alter your original ToC which comes with your "
"book. You can clear your <b>Custom table of contents</b> from this same menu "
"(in case you want to create a new one). And you can disable this feature "
"completely in the same way you enabled it, if you want to return to the "
"original ToC. Note that if you disable this feature after creating a custom "
"ToC to return to the original one, your custom ToC will not be deleted. You "
"can still switch between the original and your custom ToC."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1584-5
msgid "Excluding sections of your book: CUSTOM HIDDEN FLOWS"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1586-5
msgid ""
"Some books or documents might contain long footnotes or bibliography "
"sections. Like a scientific book which is 250 pages long but last 50 pages "
"are Appendices, Index and References. Normally these pages are included in "
"the progress bar and reading time calculations since they are part of the "
"book. But generally these sections exist as a reference and they are not "
"read completely so you might want to exclude them to make your remaining "
"page count and time estimates more accurate. Or maybe you have an anthology "
"book which contain some stories you have already read. <span class=\"ui\""
">Custom hidden flows</span> feature of KOReader allows you to exclude these "
"kind of parts of your book."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1588-5
msgid ""
"Have a look at the image for an overview of the process. Steps will be "
"explained after the image:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1593-5
msgid "How to exclude a section by creating a hidden flow"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ol.li:1595-9
msgid "Go to the first page of the section you want to exclude"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ol.li:1596-9
msgid "Open the <span class=\"ui\">Page browser</span> via:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ol.li.div:1598-13
msgctxt "user_guide/en.html+html.body.div.div.ol.li.div:1598-13"
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/top_bookmark.svg\" "
"style=\"width:26px;\"> → Page browser"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ol.li:1600-9
msgid ""
"Long press on the page thumbnail that you want to be the beginning of your "
"excluded section and select <span class=\"ui\">Start hidden flow here</span> "
"item from the popup menu."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ol.li:1601-9
msgid ""
"You will see that the pages starting from your selection now have a gray "
"hatched background."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ol.li:1602-9
msgid ""
"Now go to the last page of your excluded section. You can navigate there "
"from the <span class=\"ui\">Page browser</span> or using other ways like "
"<span class=\"ui\">Book map, Skim widget</span> etc."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ol.li:1603-9
msgid ""
"Once you are at the last page of your excluded section, open the <span class="
"\"ui\">Page browser</span> again (if you are not already in it)."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ol.li:1604-9
msgid ""
"Find the last page of your hidden section and long press on the <b>next "
"page</b>. Choose <span class=\"ui\">Restart regular flow here</span> from "
"the popup menu. You will see that the background of the remaining pages will "
"return to normal color, indicating the end of hidden flow and the beginning "
"of regular flow."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1607-5
msgid "Working with the hidden sections"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1608-5
msgid ""
"When you create a hidden flow section as described above, KOReader’s "
"behavior will be similar to the situation as if you removed a section of a "
"paper book by cutting it out:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:1610-9
msgid ""
"These hidden flow sections will be skipped when turning pages. For example "
"assume that you created a hidden flow for <b>Chapter 10</b>. Now you are on "
"the last page of <b>Chapter 9</b>. When you turn the page, you will see "
"<b>Chapter 11</b>."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:1611-9
msgid ""
"Page numbering will continue as if these hidden flow sections <b>do not "
"exist</b>."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:1612-9
msgid ""
"These hidden sections will not be shown in your <span class=\"ui\">Progress "
"bar</span> (but read the explanation below) and will not be considered in "
"<b>time to read</b> calculations. But they will still be visible in the "
"<span class=\"ui\">Skim widget</span>."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:1613-9
msgid ""
"Following direct links to the pages included in these hidden flow sections "
"will still work. Also you can still reach these sections from the <span "
"class=\"ui\">Table of contents, Book map, Page browser, Skim widget</span>."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1616-5
msgid ""
"As we said above, your hidden flows will be excluded from your <span class="
"\"ui\">Progress bar</span>. But if you jump to one of your hidden sections "
"using any of the methods mentioned above, your Progress bar temporarily "
"becomes this hidden section’s progress bar. You can imagine this as the "
"progress bar is zooming into that hidden flow section. If you exit out of "
"this hidden section by turning the page at the end of it, or using other "
"navigation tools, your Progress bar will go back to showing the whole book "
"again (with your custom hidden flows again not visible)."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1619-5
msgid "Removing and cleaning up hidden sections"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1620-5
msgid ""
"You can remove individual hidden flow sections from the <span class=\"ui\""
">Page browser</span> in the same way you created them. You can also clear "
"all of them at once with the menu item:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:1622-5
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/top_bookmark.svg\" "
"style=\"width:26px;\"> → Settings → Custom layout features → Clear all "
"marked pages"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1624-5
msgid ""
"As you work on creating hidden flows by tagging pages as <span class=\"ui\""
">Start hidden flow</span> or <span class=\"ui\">Restart regular flow</span>, "
"some of the previously made ones may stop having an effect. For example in "
"the case that you make <span class=\"ui\">Start hidden flow</span> a few "
"pages before an existing <span class=\"ui\">Start hidden flow</span>, that "
"existing one is no longer involved. This overlapping or obsolete tags are "
"remembered for practical purposes. Again in the previous example, if you end "
"that second hidden flow before the existing-but-no-longer-involved Start "
"hidden flow, this deactive one will be involved again. You can clear all "
"these inactive markers if they interfere with your custom flows, or once you "
"finish making your hidden flows and happy with the results:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:1626-5
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/top_bookmark.svg\" "
"style=\"width:26px;\"> → Settings → Custom layout features → Clear inactive "
"marked pages"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1629-5
msgid "Hidden sections and progress bar"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1630-5
msgid ""
"As we said above, your hidden flows will be excluded from your Progress bar. "
"But if you jump to one of your hidden sections using any of the methods "
"mentioned above, your Progress bar temporarily becomes this hidden section’s "
"progress bar. You can imagine this like the progress bar is zooming into "
"that hidden flow section. If you exit out of this hidden section by turning "
"the page at the end of it, or using other navigation tools, your Progress "
"bar will go back to showing the whole book again (with your custom hidden "
"flows again not visible)."
