#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1639-5
msgctxt "user_guide/en.html+html.body.div.div:1639-5"
msgid "BOOKMARKS, HIGHLIGHTING AND NOTES"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1641-5
msgid ""
"KOReader gives you options to interact with your book like you can do with a "
"real book:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1644-5
msgid ""
"<b>Bookmarks:</b> You can add (and remove) a bookmark by pressing the upper "
"right corner. This is the equivalent of folding the corner of a page on a "
"real book and shows a similar icon when you enable it."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1646-5
msgid ""
"<b>Highlights:</b> You can highlight text in 4 different styles. In the "
"image below, you can see a normal paragraph followed by different styles of "
"highlights. <span class=\"ui\">Lighten</span> (with gray background), <span "
"class=\"ui\">Underline, Strikeout</span> and <span class=\"ui\""
">Invert</span>."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1651-5
msgid ""
"You can use all these styles at the same time, like they are different "
"colored highlight markers. Or you can decide your favorite style and set it "
"as default from this menu by long pressing:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:1653-5
msgctxt "user_guide/en.html+html.body.div.div.div:1653-5"
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/top_document.svg\" "
"style=\"width:26px;\"> → Highlight style"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1655-5
msgid ""
"<b>Notes:</b> You can also add notes to your highlights. Just tap on a "
"highlight and choose <span class=\"ui\">Add note</span> from the popup menu. "
"You can also choose a <span class=\"ui\">Note marker</span> that shows which "
"highlights contain a note. There are three styles: <span class=\"ui\""
">Underline, Side line</span> and <span class=\"ui\">Side mark</span> (which "
"is the pencil icon shown on the right side of the picture below):"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1655-427
msgid ""
"To enable this feature and choose a <span class=\"ui\">Note marker</span> "
"style, go to:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:1661-5
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/top_document.svg\" "
"style=\"width:26px;\"> → Highlight style → Note marker"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1665-5
msgid "How to highlight"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1667-5
msgid "KOReader has two highlighting modes for different use cases:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1669-5
msgid ""
"<span class=\"ui\">Normal mode</span> is similar to selecting a text with "
"your finger on a phone/tablet and more suitable if your highlights are "
"shorter than one page."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1670-5
msgid ""
"<span class=\"ui\">Select and highlight mode</span> is more suitable for "
"highlighting longer passages which cross page boundaries. It might also work "
"better if you have touch screen sensitivity problems or motor control issues "
"with your hands. Because in this highlight mode you don’t need to drag your "
"finger along the screen."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1673-5
msgid "Normal mode"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1675-5
msgid ""
"This mode is similar to selecting a text with your finger on a phone/tablet."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ol.li:1678-9
msgid "Long-press on the starting word"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ol.li:1679-9
msgid "Move your finger to the end of the passage"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ol.li:1680-9
msgid "Release finger"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1682-5
msgid ""
"When you reach page boundaries, KOReader will turn the page for you to "
"continue highlighting <b>(only in EPUB/HTML documents)</b>. You can disable "
"this feature from:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:1684-5
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/gear.svg\" style="
"\"width:26px;\"> → Taps and gestures → Long-press on text → Auto-scroll when "
"selection reaches a corner"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1688-5
msgid "Select and highlight mode"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:1691-5
msgid ""
"<span class=\"label_blue\">INFO</span> If you have dictionary lookup enabled "
"when long pressing a word, you have to drag your finger to initiate this "
"mode."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:1694-5
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/gear.svg\" style="
"\"width:26px;\"> → Taps and gestures → Long-press on text → Dictionary on "
"single word selection"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ol.li:1699-5
msgid ""
"Long-press (or drag if dictionary lookup is enabled as described above) on "
"the starting word, popup menu will show up."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ol.li:1700-5
msgid ""
"Tap on <span class=\"ui\">Select</span>, now you are in highlighting mode. "
"When you are in this mode, you will see an indicator at the upper left "
"corner of the screen (which you can tap on it to get more information). You "
"can cancel highlighting by tapping on the beginning of highlight again. You "
"can turn pages with taps/swipes and freely navigate the document (TOC, skim "
"etc) in this mode."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ol.li:1701-5
msgid ""
"Long-press (or drag if dictionary lookup is enabled as described above) on "
"the ending word for your highlight, menu will show up again."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ol.li:1702-5
msgid ""
"Tap <span class=\"ui\">Highlight</span> this time to finish highlighting the "
"passage."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1705-5
msgid ""
"This dialog normally opens at the center of the screen. If you want this "
"dialog to open closer to your highlight location, you can change the center "
"option here to gesture position (located on the second page of this menu):"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:1707-5
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/gear.svg\" style="
"\"width:26px;\">→ Taps and Gestures → Long-press on text → Highlight dialog "
"position"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:1709-5
msgid ""
"<span class=\"label_green\">TIP</span> There is a <b>faster</b> method for "
"this mode if you don’t need <b>long-press menu items</b> shown above. You "
"can disable the popup menu completely so when you long-press on a word you "
"will immediately enter the <span class=\"ui\">Select and highlight</span> "
"mode. This method is much faster and you can highlight any length of text "
"with just two taps. To use this method enable this option:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:1712-5
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/gear.svg\" style="
"\"width:26px;\"> → Taps and gestures → Long-press on text → Select and "
"highlight"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:1714-5
msgid ""
"<span class=\"label_green\">TIP</span> KOReader can highlight a passage in "
"different styles. If you use <span class=\"ui\">Lighten</span> option, text "
"background will be gray. Due to e-ink limitations, screens can’t change from "
"white to gray directly, so highlighted part first has to turn black and then "
"gray. If you want to avoid this flashing, you can choose <span class=\"ui\""
">Inverted</span> as your highlight style. In this mode text background will "
"be black so it can be set without flashing. You can adjust these "
"highlighting options via:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:1717-5
msgctxt "user_guide/en.html+html.body.div.div.div:1717-5"
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/top_document.svg\" "
"style=\"width:26px;\"> → Highlight style"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:1719-5
msgid ""
"<span class=\"label_green\">TIP</span> You can add multiple highlights and "
"notes to the same section of text. If they are overlapping, when you tap on "
"a highlight you will be presented with a menu to choose which highlight you "
"want to edit."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1723-5
msgid "Selecting punctuation"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1725-5
msgid ""
"When you are highlighting, KOReader tries to include the related punctuation "
"marks around your selection. For example if you highlight from the first "
"word to the last word of a sentence, KOReader will automatically include the "
"punctuation marks at the both ends of the sentence to your highlight."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1728-5
msgid ""
"But if you start highlighting from the middle of a sentence, period at the "
"end <b>will not be included</b> because KOReader assumes that you want to "
"make a partial highlight. So if you want the punctuation marks to be added "
"to your highlight, be sure that you select the <b>whole sentence</b>. Also "
"you can add these marks later by long pressing the <span class=\"ui\""
">Highlight edit</span> buttons."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1731-5
msgid "Editing a highlight"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1734-5
msgid ""
"When you tap on an already highlighted text <b>(without a note)</b>, you "
"will see this popup menu. <span class=\"ui\">Delete</span> and <span class="
"\"ui\">Add note</span> items are clear. Bottom row menu items are used to "
"extend or shrink the highlight."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:1738-5
msgid ""
"<span class=\"label_blue\">INFO</span> This adjustment works only on "
"reflowable documents like EPUBs. If you want to extend or shrink a highlight "
"on PDFs, you have to delete it and highlight again due to the limitations of "
"the PDF format."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1740-5
msgid ""
"When you tap on an already highlighted text <b>with a note added</b>, you "
"will see this popup menu. Tap on <span class=\"ui\">Edit highlight</span> to "
"open the menu above where you can edit both the highlight and the contained "
"note:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1744-5
msgid ""
"On your <span class=\"ui\">Bookmarks</span> page you can filter the view to "
"see only one type of bookmark by pressing the menu icon ( <img class="
"\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/top_hamburger.svg\" style=\"width:26px;\"> ) "
"You can also filter by highlight style:"
msgstr ""

