msgctxt "user_guide/en.html+html.body.div.div:1892-5"
msgid "Explanations Of Pdf Specific Bottom Menu Items"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1897-5
msgid ""
"<span class=\"ui\">CONTRAST</span> This setting adjusts black levels in your "
"document. Be aware that same contrast value applies to both text and images "
"in your document. If you set it very high, your images may become too dark "
"to be readable."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1898-5
msgid ""
"<span class=\"ui\">DEWATERMARK</span> Removes watermarks from the rendered "
"document. It can also be used to remove gray backgrounds. This feature can "
"convert a grayscale or color document to black & white to produce more "
"contrast for easier reading."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1899-5
msgid ""
"<span class=\"ui\">RENDER QUALITY</span> <b>(REFLOW MODE)</b> Sets the "
"quality of text and image extraction processing and output. <span class="
"\"ui\">HIGH</span> is more pleasing but it can be much slower (several "
"seconds for page turn) than <span class=\"ui\">DEFAULT</span> depending on "
"your document. If your PDF/DJVU files are slow, this is the first setting "
"you should check."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1905-5
msgid ""
"<span class=\"ui\">DOCUMENT LANGUAGE</span> Sets the language to be used by "
"the OCR engine."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1906-5
msgid ""
"<span class=\"ui\">FORCED OCR</span> Force the use of OCR even if the "
"document has a text layer"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1907-5
msgid ""
"<span class=\"ui\">WRITING DIRECTION</span> <b>(REFLOW MODE)</b> Text "
"direction of original document. Set to RTL for languages like Arabic and "
"Hebrew."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1908-5
msgid ""
"<span class=\"ui\">DOCUMENT COLUMNS</span> <b>(REFLOW MODE)</b> Number of "
"text columns in the original document."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1914-5
msgid ""
"<span class=\"ui\">AUTO STRAIGHTEN</span> feature can straighten the pages "
"of a problematic document, for example pages of a PDF which are scanned with "
"an angle. It is available in <b>PDF, DJVU, CBZ/CBT</b> documents and "
"<b>image</b> files. To enable, choose the maximum tilt angle which KOReader "
"will try to correct. If it doesn’t correct you might have to choose a bigger "
"angle. Note that this feature <b>might slow down your reader</b> depending "
"on several factors."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1917-5
msgctxt "user_guide/en.html+html.body.div.div:1917-5"
msgid "OCR (Optical Character Recognition)"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1918-5
msgid ""
"<b>OCR (Optical Character Recognition)</b> is the process of extracting text "
"from images into machine readable format. In KOReader context, it is "
"generally used for extracting text from scanned book pages in PDF files. "
"KOReader relies on <span class=\"external\">Tesseract Open Source OCR "
"Engine</span> for this task (<a href="
"\"https://github.com/tesseract-ocr/tessdoc\">https://github.com/"
"tesseract-ocr/tessdoc</a>)."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1921-5
msgid "In order to use this feature you need to:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ol.li:1923-9
msgid ""
"Install <span class=\"external\">Tesseract</span> language data to your "
"KOReader"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ol.li:1924-9
msgid ""
"Add newly installed languages to koreader/defaults.lua configuration file ("
"necessary only if your language is other than English or Chinese)"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:1928-5
msgid ""
"<span class=\"label_blue\">INFO</span> Buttons on OCR menu <b>will not "
"function</b> until you install the necessary Tesseract files. Details of "
"this process can be read in the related wiki page: <a href=\"https://"
"github.com/koreader/koreader/wiki/Dictionary-support#dictionary-lookups-in-"
"scanned-pages\">https://github.com/koreader/koreader/wiki/Dictionary-support"
"#dictionary-lookups-in-scanned-pages</a>"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1932-5
msgctxt "user_guide/en.html+html.body.div.div:1932-5"
msgid "Panel Zoom (manga/comic)"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1933-5
msgid ""
"This feature makes reading comic books easier on smaller screens. You can "
"enable it while you are reading a <b>PDF, DJVU, CBZ or CBT</b> document via:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:1936-5
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/top_document.svg\" "
"style=\"width:26px;\"> → Panel Zoom (manga/comic)"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1938-5
msgid ""
"When this option is enabled, KOReader tries to find the boundaries of "
"rectangular panels on the screen. If you long-tap on a panel, KOReader zooms "
"in to that panel. As you can guess, this feature works best with comics that "
"has clean panel boundaries. Procedure can be seen below:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1942-5
msgid ""
"If you want to use this feature with other file types like EPUB, FB2, HTML "
"or image files, you should open the file with a different engine: In the "
"<span class=\"ui\">File Browser</span> long-tap on the file name, tap <span "
"class=\"ui\">Open with…</span> and select <span class=\"ui\">MuPDF</span>."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1950-1
msgctxt "user_guide/en.html+html.body.div.div:1950-1"
msgid "PREPARING AND TRANSFERRING YOUR DOCUMENTS"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1952-1
msgctxt "user_guide/en.html+html.body.div.div:1952-1"
msgid "Transferring books to your reader"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1953-1
msgid ""
"KOReader supports <b>PDF, EPUB, DJVU, MOBI, CBZ, CBT, DOCX, RTF, HTML, TXT, "
"XPS, FB2, PDB, CHM and ZIP</b> files."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1956-1
msgid ""
"KOReader can reflow PDF documents (this option can be found in the bottom "
"menu while reading a fixed-layout document like PDF) to make them suitable "
"for the small screens of e-readers. But for best results, you may want to "
"convert your documents into more flexible EPUB format. You can use <span "
"class=\"external\">Calibre</span> (<a href=\"https://calibre-ebook.com/\""
">https://calibre-ebook.com/</a>) for all kinds of conversion between formats."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1958-1
msgid ""
"There are many ways to transfer your documents to your device. Note that you "
"may need to restart KOReader to index the transferred documents (or refresh "
"directory if you have Pocketbook/Android)."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1960-1
msgid ""
"In addition to transferring files the same way you would with the built-in "
"reader application, other options are available depending on your device:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ol.li:1964-5
msgid ""
"<b>USB mass storage mode within KOReader:</b> This mode is available for "
"KOBO and some CERVANTES devices."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ol.li:1965-5
msgid ""
"<b>Cloud storage (<span class=\"external\">Dropbox</span>/FTP/Webdav):</b> "
"To use this function you have to add accounts for a cloud storage server via "
"menu shown below. Process is explained via <span class=\"ui\">INFO</span> "
"buttons while adding accounts:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ol.li.div:1967-5
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU (in File Browser) → <img class=\"img_inline\" src="
"\"pictures/top_tools.svg\" style=\"width:26px;\"> → Cloud storage"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ol.li:1970-5
msgid ""
"<b>SSH/SFTP access:</b> KOReader can act like an <b>SSH server</b>, which "
"you can access from a computer to transfer files (available on Kobo, Kindle, "
"Cervantes). You can use an SFTP application (like <span class=\"external\""
">Filezilla</span>) or access via your file manager if your operating system "
"supports. Check wiki for how-to: <a href="
"\"https://github.com/koreader/koreader/wiki/SSH\">https://github.com/"
"koreader/koreader/wiki/SSH</a>"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ol.li:1971-5
msgid ""
"<b>Calibre transfer:</b> With the <span class=\"external\">Calibre plugin</"
"span> you can send documents from your Calibre Library directly to your "
"KOReader devices via a wifi connection. Check wiki for how-to: <a href="
"\"https://github.com/koreader/koreader/wiki/Calibre-wireless-connection\""
">https://github.com/koreader/koreader/wiki/Calibre-wireless-connection</a>"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ol.li:1972-5
msgid ""
"<b>News downloader:</b> With this plugin you can download <b>RSS and Atom</"
"b> news entries as HTML files. Check wiki for how-to: <a href="
"\"https://github.com/koreader/koreader/wiki/News-downloader\">https://"
"github.com/koreader/koreader/wiki/News-downloader</a>"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ol.li:1973-5
msgid ""
"<b>Wallabag:</b> With this plugin you can retrieve articles from <span class="
"\"external\">Wallabag</span>, a server based read-it-later service like "
"Pocket. Check wiki page for more info: <a href="
"\"https://github.com/koreader/koreader/wiki/Wallabag\">https://github.com/"
"koreader/koreader/wiki/Wallabag</a>"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1977-1
msgid "Custom book cover using a screenshot"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1978-1
msgid ""
"Some books don’t come with proper book covers. Or they may have their cover "
"on the second page so it doesn’t show up properly. Or maybe the cover is not "
"suitable for e-ink (too light or dark). Or you prefer to set some image from "
"the book as cover."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1981-1
msgid ""
"In situations like this you can quickly take a screenshot and set it as the "
"current book’s cover. Screenshot gesture is a <b>long diagonal swipe</b> by "
"default. Also <b>touching opposing diagonal corners</b> will take a "
"screenshot. You can use this second shortcut when viewing an image. After "
"taking your screenshot you can select <span class=\"ui\">Set as book cover</"
"span> from the dialog."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1983-1
msgid "You can remove this custom book cover here:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:1985-1
msgctxt "user_guide/en.html+html.body.div.div.div:1985-1"
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/top_hamburger.svg\" "
"style=\"width:26px;\"> → Book information"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1987-1
msgid ""
"On the book information page, long-press on the <span class=\"ui\">Cover "
"image</span> item and then select <span class=\"ui\">Reset custom</span>."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:1989-1
msgid ""
"You can also reset the book cover with the <span class=\"ui\">Reset</span> "
"dialog, which you can access by long-pressing the filename in the <span "
"class=\"ui\">File Browser</span>."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:1991-1
msgid ""
"<span class=\"label_red\">WARNING</span> Be very careful when using this "
"<b>Reset</b> dialog and be sure that only <b>Custom cover image</b> item is "
"checked otherwise you can reset everything related to your book accidentally."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1997-1
msgctxt "user_guide/en.html+html.body.div.div:1997-1"
msgid "Optimizing EPUB/PDF documents for your mobile reader device"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:1999-1
msgid ""
"Most widely used applications for converting or optimizing your document for "
"your mobile reading device are <span class=\"external\">Calibre</span> ("
"<b>EPUB, Kindle</b> focused) and <span class=\"external\">K2pdfopt</span> "
"(<b>PDF</b> focused)."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2002-1
msgid ""
"<span class=\"external\">Calibre</span> can convert your documents between "
"many formats. It also has a built-in editor that allows you to edit e-books ("
"and fix problems) in the most popular e-book formats, EPUB and Kindle. <a "
"href=\"https://calibre-ebook.com/\">https://calibre-ebook.com/</a>"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2004-1
msgid ""
"<span class=\"external\">K2pdfopt</span> optimizes PDF/DJVU files for mobile "
"e-readers and smartphones. It works well on multi-column PDF/DJVU files and "
"can re-flow text even on scanned PDF files. It can also be used as a general "
"PDF copying/cropping/re-sizing/OCR-ing manipulation tool. <a href="
"\"https://www.willus.com/k2pdfopt/\">https://www.willus.com/k2pdfopt/</a>"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2006-1
msgid ""
"<span class=\"external\">OCRmyPDF</span> is a command line application which "
"can add an OCR text layer to scanned PDF files (containing only images "
"without text), allowing them to be searched or copy-pasted. It can "
"especially be useful for reading old scanned books. It can also optimize the "
"images for a smaller file size. <a href="
"\"https://github.com/ocrmypdf/OCRmyPDF\">https://github.com/ocrmypdf/"
"OCRmyPDF</a>"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2008-1
msgid ""
"<span class=\"external\">SingleFile</span> is a browser extension for "
"<b>Mozilla Firefox, Google Chrome</b> and <b>Microsoft Edge</b>. This "
"extension allows saving a web page as a single .html file with all resources "
"(images, stylesheets, scripts) embedded. <a href="
"\"https://github.com/gildas-lormeau/SingleFile#install\">https://github.com/"
"gildas-lormeau/SingleFile#install</a>"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:2011-1
msgctxt "user_guide/en.html+html.body.div.div:2011-1"
msgid "ZIP file support"
msgstr "Book map controls"

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:2013-1
msgid ""
"KOReader can read files stored/compressed in <b>ZIP</b> files. A ZIP file "
"can contain many types of documents like html, txt or images. KOReader can "
"open your ZIP file properly if you give it a hint for the type of file in "
"the ZIP archive. If you give your file only a <b>.zip</b> extension, "
"KOReader will assume that this archive contains images and try to open it "
"like a <b>CBZ</b> file."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2016-1
msgid ""
"<span class=\"ui\">DEFAULT CASE:</span> yourfilename<b>.zip</b> - Assumed to "
"be a zip file of images (and opened by <span class=\"ui\">MuPDF "
"engine</span>)"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2018-1
msgid ""
"If your zip file contains one of these types (instead of just images), "
"please name it accordingly:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:2021-5
msgid "<b>FictionBook</b> - yourfilename.<b>fb2.zip</b>"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:2022-5
msgid "<b>HTML</b> - yourfilename.htm.zip / yourfilename.<b>html.zip</b>"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:2023-5
msgid "<b>Text log files</b> - yourfilename.<b>log.zip</b>"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:2024-5
msgid "<b>Markdown</b> - yourfilename.<b>md.zip</b>"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:2025-5
msgid "<b>Rich Text Format</b> - yourfilename.<b>rtf.zip</b>"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:2026-5
msgid "<b>Plain text</b> - yourfilename.<b>txt.zip</b>"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2029-1
msgid ""
"If the documents are not named like this, the wrong reader/format engine is "
"likely to be used and you will see the <span class=\"ui\">No reader engine "
"for this file or invalid file</span> message. You can rename this file as "
"explained above or long-press the filename and then choose <span class=\"ui\""
">Open with...</span> to select the correct engine."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:2033-1
msgctxt "user_guide/en.html+html.body.div.div:2033-1"
msgid "Optimizing manga for your mobile reader device"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:2035-1
msgid ""
"If you like reading manga books on your e-ink device there are some tips "
"that can make your experience better. Preparing your own manga files is the "
"best solution if you're not satisfied with how comics look on your device."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:2038-1
msgid "File type"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2039-1
msgid ""
"File types like MOBI and EPUB are not suitable for handling primarily image "
"content (e.g., manga/comics). <b>MOBI</b> support in KOReader is minimal to "
"nonexistent, and <b>EPUB’s</b> text rendering priorities can cause problems "
"when showing full-page images. For further technical details:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2041-1
msgid ""
"<a href="
"\"https://github.com/koreader/koreader/issues/9163#issuecomment-1146637205\""
">https://github.com/koreader/koreader/issues/"
"9163#issuecomment-1146637205</a>)."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2044-1
msgid ""
"Your best option is building a <b>CBZ</b> file which works better in "
"KOReader. A file with <b>.cbz</b> extension is a zip file (with no "
"compression) that is a collection of images. It saves multiple images, "
"commonly <b>.png</b> or <b>.jpeg</b> files, organized into pages of the "
"comic. KOReader can also open <b>CBT</b> files, which are similar to <b>CBZ</"
"b> files but use <b>TAR</b> archive format."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2046-1
msgid ""
"Easiest way to convert a manga to <b>CBZ</b> is to get the manga as images "
"from various websites, then convert them using <span class=\"external\""
">Kindle Comic Converter</span> (<a href=\"https://github.com/ciromattia/kcc\""
">https://github.com/ciromattia/kcc</a>). There are some useful settings like "
"<b>auto-rotating two-page splits to landscape and applying dithering</b> so "
"that eink-rendered gradients are smoothly dithered without jagged layers."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:2048-1
msgid "Resolution"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2049-1
msgid ""
"The best results can be achieved by resizing your images to exactly your e-"
"reader screen size. A screen-specific <b>CBZ</b> which targets the exact "
"screen size of the device, prevents rescaling during reading. KOReader "
"downscales your images to your screen size while reading but this is not "
"recommended because KOReader adds a dithering pass before scaling and this "
"causes loss of quality."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2051-1
msgid ""
"But if you want to use your hand made <b>CBZ</b> on more than one device or "
"you want to preserve high resolution for future proofing, your best option "
"might be to make the <b>CBZ</b> for your highest resolution device. Or pick "
"an arbitrary \"high\" resolution, possibly one that matches the source. "
"<b>300 PPI</b> or better (up to <b>450</b> or even <b>600</b>), unless the "
"source is lower of course. If we assume a screen size of <b>8\", 1500×2000</"
"b> is a good target resolution. For bigger images, you should try it on your "
"device and see whether it can deal with it. Especially old Kindles with low "
"memory can struggle with sizes like <b>3000×4000</b> for example. If you're "
"automating the process, it might be worth considering creating both a lower "
"and higher quality version (e.g., at <b>200/400</b> or <b>300/600</b> DPI)."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:2053-1
msgid ""
"<span class=\"label_blue\">INFO</span> KOReader doesn't parse <b>spine page-"
"progression-direction=\"rtl\"</b> attribute of the books. So it doesn’t "
"change page turning direction even though the file was created with right-to-"
"left reading. Users can switch this via:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:2056-1
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/gear.svg\" style="
"\"width:26px;\"> → Taps and gestures → Page turns → Invert page turn tap and "
"swipes / buttons"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:2060-1
msgid "Advanced preparation of manga"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:2062-1
msgid "The following is an example procedure to process one manga file:"
msgstr "Page Browser"

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:2065-5
msgid ""
"Download <span class=\"external\">Kindle Comic Converter (KCC)</span> from "
"<a href=\"https://github.com/ciromattia/kcc\">https://github.com/ciromattia/"
"kcc</a>"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:2066-5
msgid ""
"Download your manga from the source of your choosing (i.e. <span class="
"\"external\">HakuNeko</span>)"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:2067-5
msgid ""
"Unpack the manga file. Now you should have a directory that contains only "
"images (or subdirectories with images, no archives)"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:2068-5
msgid ""
"Process this directory with <span class=\"external\">KCC</span>. Each "
"directory will produce a single <b>CBZ</b> file, so if you want to make "
"several volumes at once, select multiple directories at once"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2071-1
msgid "Some useful settings of <span class=\"external\">KCC</span>:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2072-1
msgid ""
"<b>Spread splitter:</b> This feature detects double pages and allows you to "
"rotate or cut them in two."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2073-1
msgid ""
"<b>Upscaling:</b> Enlarge images that is smaller than your target resolution."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:2076-1
msgid "Immersive mode in KOReader"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:2078-1
msgid ""
"If you would like to enjoy your manga in a more immersive way, make sure "
"that you selected the exact same resolution as your device’s screen "
"resolution in <b>KCC</b> when creating your <b>CBZ</b> file. Also you can "
"hide the bottom progress bar while reading your manga in KOReader. So you "
"will have an immersive full screen view of your manga without obstructions."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:2083-1
msgid ""
"Extra step for smooth gradients <span class=\"warning\"><span class="
"\"label_red\">!!! ADVANCED</span></span>"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:2085-1
msgid ""
