msgctxt "user_guide/en.html+html.body.div.div:2651-5"
msgid "QUICK MENU AND PROFILES"
msgstr "<span class=\"label_green\">TIP</span> KOReader can highlight a passage in different styles. If you use <span class=\"ui\">Lighten</span> option, text background will be gray. Due to e-ink limitations, screens can’t change from white to gray directly, so highlighted part first has to turn black and then gray. If you want to avoid this flashing, you can choose <span class=\"ui\">Inverted</span> as your highlight style. In this mode text background will be black so it can be set without flashing. You can adjust these highlighting options from:"

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:2654-5
msgctxt "user_guide/en.html+html.body.div.div:2654-5"
msgid "Quick Menu"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:2655-5
msgid ""
"<span class=\"ui\">Quick Menu</span> is a recent feature of KOReader which "
"allows you to have a quickly accessible personalized menu. You can assign "
"this menu to a gesture and access it with a single swipe. You can see an "
"example menu on the right. You can even have a menu longer than your screen, "
"it is scrollable."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2658-9
msgid ""
"Basically, any action you can assign a gesture can be added to the <span "
"class=\"ui\">Quick Menu</span>. Its advantages are:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ol.li:2661-13
msgid "You don’t need to memorize lots of gestures for every action."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ol.li:2662-13
msgid ""
"Some infrequent actions may not worth a gesture but it can be too much "
"hassle to find it in the menu system. You can add this kind of rarely used "
"actions to this menu instead."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ol.li:2663-13
msgid ""
"If you are installing KOReader for a relative or friend, you can add their "
"favorite actions to this menu so they don’t even need to go into the menu "
"system while using KOReader."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2666-9
msgid "An example Quick Menu:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2671-9
msgid ""
"There are two methods for creating a <span class=\"ui\">Quick Menu</span>. "
"<b>Easy</b> and <b>Advanced</b>. If you need only one menu, <b>Easy method</"
"b> should be enough for you. If you want show different menus with different "
"gestures you need to use <b>Advanced method</b>. Another advantage of "
"<b>Advanced method</b> is that, if you want to use another gesture for your "
"menu you can easily move it to another gesture. If you want to use another "
"gesture while using the <b>Easy method</b>, you have to re-create your menu "
"under the new gesture."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:2675-9
msgid "Easy method"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ol.li:2678-17
msgid "Go to <span class=\"ui\">Gesture Manager</span> menu via:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ol.li.div:2679-21
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/gear.svg\" style="
"\"width:26px;\"> → Taps and Gestures → Gesture Manager"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ol.li:2680-17
msgid "Decide a gesture for opening your menu and tap on it."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ol.li:2681-17
msgid ""
"Choose the actions you want to see in your menu from the gesture "
"configuration menu. You can select many actions at once of course."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ol.li:2682-17
msgid ""
"After selecting all your actions, you will tell KOReader to treat this "
"gesture as a menu. You achieve this by enabling <span class=\"ui\">Show as "
"Quick Menu</span> item on the second page as you can see <b>in the picture "
"below</b>."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ol.li:2683-17
msgid ""
"You can sort your menu items with the <span class=\"ui\">Sort</span> option "
"just below it."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2685-9
msgid ""
"Now you can launch your menu with the gesture you selected. If you want to "
"change the menu items, you can open the gesture page and add/remove items."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:2690-9
msgid "Advanced method"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:2693-13
msgid ""
"<span class=\"label_blue\">INFO</span> As we said above, if you are not "
"planning to add more than one <span class=\"ui\">Quick Menu</span> you don’t "
"need this section."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2696-9
msgid ""
"<span class=\"ui\">Quick Menu</span> is actually a <span class=\"ui\""
">Profile</span> which appears on your screen as a menu. So first you have to "
"learn about <span class=\"ui\">Profiles</span>. If you already know how to "
"use <span class=\"ui\">Profiles</span>, you can continue reading, otherwise "
"jump to the <span class=\"ui\">Profiles</span> heading (next section), "
"create a <span class=\"ui\">Profile</span> with some items and come back "
"here."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2698-9
msgid ""
"We assume that you already created a <span class=\"ui\">Profile</span> as "
"instructed in the previous paragraph. Now we will turn our <span class=\"ui\""
">Profile</span> into a <span class=\"ui\">Quick Menu</span>."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2700-9
msgid ""
"1. Go to your newly created <span class=\"ui\">Profile</span> and enable "
"<span class=\"ui\">Show in action list</span> (shown in the image below). "
"This will make your <span class=\"ui\">Profile</span> visible in the <span "
"class=\"ui\">Gesture Manager</span>. Also enable <span class=\"ui\">Show as "
"Quick Menu</span> (also in the image below) so your profile will be shown as "
"a menu instead of being silently executed."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2704-9
msgid ""
"2. Now we need a way to access our menu. Go to the <span class=\"ui\""
">Gesture Manager</span> and choose a gesture from the list to assign to our "
"menu. Let’s say we want to tap the corner of the screen to show menu. Now "
"tap on <span class=\"ui\">Tap corner</span> then choose <span class=\"ui\""
">Bottom left</span>. Now tap on <span class=\"ui\">General</span> and go to "
"the second page. You will find your profile as <span class=\"ui\">Profile x</"
"span> where x is the name you gave to this <span class=\"ui\">Profile</"
"span>. Tap on its checkbox to assign your profile to this gesture."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2706-9
msgid ""
"After all the steps, now you should see your menu when you tap on the bottom "
"left corner. You can edit your menu by going to its <span class=\"ui\""
">Profile</span> page where you can add or remove items. Also there is a "
"<span class=\"ui\">Sort</span> item there so you can change the order of "
"your menu items."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2708-9
msgid ""
"As we said, a <span class=\"ui\">Quick Menu</span> is actually a <span class="
"\"ui\">Profile</span>. Which means you can have more than one menu. You can "
"create another <span class=\"ui\">Profile</span> and follow the same steps "
"to create another menu if you want."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:2711-9
msgid "Quick menu tips"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:2713-9
msgid "Keeping the menu open after use"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:2715-9
msgid ""
"Normally after selecting an item in your Quick Menu, menu disappears from "
"the screen. Sometimes you might want to keep the menu open after selecting "
"an item. This allows you to adjust settings like these examples:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:2719-13
msgid ""
"<b>Incremental changes</b>, like brightness increase/decrease, bigger/"
"smaller font size, previous/next pages or chapters, etc."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:2723-13
msgid ""
"<b>Group of options that you activate in succession</b> (but not "
"simultaneously), like <b>turning on wifi</b> and after that <b>starting the "
"SSH server</b>"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2728-9
msgid ""
"You can enable this option from the following menu if you have a <b>Gesture "
"Manager based (Easy method)</b> Quick Menu:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:2730-9
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/gear.svg\" style="
"\"width:26px;\">→ Taps and Gestures → Gesture Manager → “Your Quick Menu "
"gesture” → Keep Quick Menu open"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2732-9
msgid ""
"Or from this menu, if you have a <b>Profiles based – (Advanced method)</b> "
"Quick Menu:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:2734-9
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/top_tools.svg\" style="
"\"width:26px;\">→ Profiles → “Your Quick Menu profile” → Edit actions → Keep "
"Quick Menu open"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:2737-9
msgid "Opening Quick Menu at the gesture position"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:2739-9
msgid ""
"Normally Quick Menu opens centered at the middle of the screen. If you are "
"using your e-reader with one hand you can activate a setting which will open "
"your menu at the gesture position. This way, menu will be closer to your "
"finger and easier to access. To use this feature enable this option:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:2742-9
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/gear.svg\" style="
"\"width:26px;\">→ Taps and Gestures → Gesture Manager → “Your Quick Menu "
"gesture” → Anchor Quick Menu to gesture position"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:2744-9
msgid ""
"<span class=\"label_blue\">INFO</span> This is available only in a Quick "
"Menu which is created via Gesture Manager (Easy method above)."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:2750-9
msgctxt "user_guide/en.html+html.body.div.div:2750-9"
msgid "Profiles"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:2751-9
msgid ""
"A profile is basically a collection of actions that can be triggered with a "
"single tap (like a macro)."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2753-9
msgid ""
"As an example, imagine that when reading some type of books, you always:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:2755-13
