#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2870-9
msgid "Some notable examples of these external plugins:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:2872-13
msgid ""
"<span class=\"external\">AskGPT:</span> You can ask questions to <span class="
"\"external\">ChatGPT</span> about parts of your book. You can also use this "
"plugin to simplify, explain, discuss or translate text to other languages. "
"<a href=\"https://github.com/drewbaumann/AskGPT\">https://github.com/"
"drewbaumann/AskGPT</a>"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:2873-13
msgid ""
"<span class=\"external\">Anki plugin for KOReader:</span> KOReader plugin "
"enabling <span class=\"external\">Anki</span> (an open-source flashcard "
"software) card generations for words looked up in the internal dictionary. "
"<a href=\"https://github.com/Ajatt-Tools/anki.koplugin\">https://github.com/"
"Ajatt-Tools/anki.koplugin</a>"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:2874-13
msgid ""
"<span class=\"external\">Zotero for KOReader:</span> This addon allows you "
"to browse your <span class=\"external\">Zotero</span> (an open-source "
"reference management software) collections from KOReader. <a href="
"\"https://github.com/stelzch/zotero.koplugin\">https://github.com/stelzch/"
"zotero.koplugin</a>"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2877-9
msgid ""
"Also you can click this link to open a search page on <span class="
"\"external\">Github</span> to discover more KOReader plugin projects: <a "
"href=\"https://github.com/search?q=koplugin&type=repositories\">https://"
"github.com/search?q=koplugin&type;=repositories</a>"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:2881-9
msgctxt "user_guide/en.html+html.body.div.div:2881-9"
msgid "List of internal plugins"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2883-9
msgid ""
"<b> Auto frontlight </b> - Automatically toggles the frontlight according to "
"ambient light level (Only available on Kindle Voyage and Oasis)"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2884-9
msgid ""
"<b> Auto warmth and night mode </b> - Allows you to adjust frontlight warmth "
"in devices with natural (yellow/orange) light and set Night Mode "
"automatically according to a schedule"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2885-9
msgid ""
"<b> Auto power save </b> - Puts the device into standby, suspend or power "
"off after specified periods of inactivity"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2886-9
msgid ""
"<b> Autosuspend </b> - Suspend device after chosen period of inactivity ("
"available on all e-ink devices except android os)"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2887-9
msgid ""
"<b> Autoturn </b> - Automatically turns the page after a set period of time"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2888-9
msgid ""
"<b> Background runner </b> - Service to other plugins: Allows tasks to run "
"regularly in the background."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2889-9
msgid ""
"<b> Battery statistics </b> - Collects and displays battery usage statistics "
"of your device"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2890-9
msgid "<b> Book shortcuts </b> - Allows adding a book shortcut to a gesture"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2891-9
msgid ""
"<b> Calibre </b> - You can send documents from your Calibre Library directly "
"to your KOReader devices via WiFi connection. Check the wiki for how-to: <a "
"href="
"\"https://github.com/koreader/koreader/wiki/Calibre-wireless-connection\""
">https://github.com/koreader/koreader/wiki/Calibre-wireless-connection</a>"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2892-9
msgid ""
"<b> Cover browser </b> - Allows cover display modes for file browser and "
"history"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2893-9
msgid ""
"<b> Cover image </b> - Saves the cover image of the current book as a file ("
"available on Android/PocketBook/reMarkable devices)"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2894-9
msgid ""
"<b> Export highlights </b> - Export highlights and notes to local files or "
"to Joplin (a note taking application)"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2895-9
msgid ""
"<b> Flashcard trainer </b> - Show flashcards using spaced repetition (SM2) "
"of highlight from your library"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2896-9
msgid "<b> Gestures </b> - Provide gesture support for KOReader"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2897-9
msgid ""
"<b> Japanese support </b> - Japanese language support for KOReader that "
"extends built-in dictionary and selection system"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2898-9
msgid ""
"<b> Keep alive </b> - Keeps the device awake to prevent automatic WiFi "
"disconnects"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2899-9
msgid "<b> Move to archive </b> - Moves current document to archive folder"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2900-9
msgid ""
"<b> News Downloader </b> - Retrieves RSS and Atom news entries and saves "
"them as HTML files. Check the wiki for how-to: <a href="
"\"https://github.com/koreader/koreader/wiki/News-downloader\">https://"
"github.com/koreader/koreader/wiki/News-downloader</a>"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2901-9
msgid "<b> OPDS </b> - Allows you to download books from online catalogs"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2902-9
msgid ""
"<b> Perception expander </b> - Allows using peripheral vision to read more "
"quickly. Check this YouTube video to see how it works: <a href="
"\"https://youtu.be/jeOHqI9SqOI?t=137\">How to Triple Your Reading Speed in "
"20 Minutes (Tim Ferriss)</a>"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2903-9
msgid ""
"<b> Profiles </b> - Allows combining multiple settings to make switchable "
"profiles"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2904-9
msgid ""
"<b> Progress sync </b> - Synchronize your reading progress across different "
"KOReader devices. Check the wiki for how-to: <a href="
"\"https://github.com/koreader/koreader/wiki/Progress-sync\">https://"
"github.com/koreader/koreader/wiki/Progress-sync</a>"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2905-9
msgid "<b> QR from clipboard </b> - Generates a QR code from clipboard content"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2906-9
msgid ""
"<b> Read timer </b> - A countdown timer to display a message after a user "
"defined time"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2907-9
msgid ""
"<b> Reading statistics </b> - Calculates reading sessions statistics and "
"reading speed for use in chapter/book remaining time estimations"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2908-9
msgid ""
"<b> SSH </b> - Allows access to your device over SSH protocol. You can "
"access via FTP applications or even your file manager if it supports. Check "
"the wiki page for how-to: <a href="
"\"https://github.com/koreader/koreader/wiki/SSH\">https://github.com/"
"koreader/koreader/wiki/SSH</a>"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2909-9
msgid ""
"<b> System statistics </b> - You can see your CPU/RAM/BATTERY info via this "
"plugin under:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:2910-9
msgctxt "user_guide/en.html+html.body.div.div.div:2910-9"
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/top_hamburger.svg\" "
"style=\"width:26px;\"> → Help → System statistics"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2911-9
msgid ""
"<b> Terminal emulator </b> - Starts a shell (command prompt) on your device "
"that can run full terminal apps"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2912-9
msgid ""
"<b> Text editor </b> - A basic text editor to create and edit plain text "
"files"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2913-9
msgid "<b> Time sync </b> - Synchronizes the device time with NTP servers"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2914-9
msgid ""
"<b> Tweak document settings </b> - Allows tweaking settings of a document "
"before it is loaded based on external factors"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2915-9
msgid ""
"<b> Wallabag </b> - Downloads the latest articles from a Wallabag server as "
"individual EPUB files. Check the wiki page for more info: <a href="
"\"https://github.com/koreader/koreader/wiki/Wallabag\">https://github.com/"
"koreader/koreader/wiki/Wallabag</a>"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:2918-9
msgid ""
"User patches<span class=\"warning\"><span class=\"label_red\">!!! "
"ADVANCED</span></span>"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:2920-9
msgid ""
"User patches are small files written in <b>Lua</b> language. They can change "
"the functionality of KOReader without modifying your installation "
"permanently. They can be written by developers, other users or you can write "
"one yourself (if you have the necessary extensive knowledge about the "
"KOReader internals)."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2923-9
msgid ""
"You can find a current list of <span class=\"ui\">User patches</span> in the "
"related <b>GitHub</b> wiki page:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2925-9
msgid "https://github.com/koreader/koreader/wiki/User-patches"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2927-9
msgid ""
"and in the <b>issues</b> list under the <span class=\"ui\">User patch "
"available</span> tag:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2929-9
msgid ""
"https://github.com/koreader/koreader/"
"issues?q=+label%3A%22User+patch+available%22"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:2932-9
msgid "Basic usage – Adding an already written patch to your KOReader:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ol.li:2935-13
msgid ""
"Create a directory named <span class=\"ui\">patches</span> under <span class="
"\"ui\">koreader directory</span> on your device (On Android this folder is "
"located on the SD-card)"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ol.li:2936-13
msgid ""
"Download and put the patch file with <b>.lua</b> extension in this <span "
"class=\"ui\">patches</span> directory"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ol.li:2937-13
msgctxt "user_guide/en.html+html.body.div.div.ol.li:2937-13"
msgid "Restart KOReader"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:2941-9
msgid "Patch manager"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2943-9
msgid ""
"When you create a patches directory as instructed, a new plugin named <span "
"class=\"ui\">Patch Management</span> becomes available in the plugins menu "
"after restarting KOReader. With this plugin you can see the list and status "
"of your user patches and enable/disable them. You can tap <span class=\"ui\""
">About patch manager</span> menu item to see more info."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:2945-9
msgid "Naming the patch"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2947-9
msgid ""
"Execution order of a patch is determined by the first digit of the number in "
"the patch name. For example: <span class=\"ui\">2-TOC-title-patch.lua</span> "
"If there are several patches starting with the same digit, the execution "
"order is the natural order "
"<b>(1&lt;10&lt;11&lt;12&lt;13&lt;…&lt;109&lt;…&lt;10010)</b>. If you are "
"just downloading an already made patch you don’t need to change the file "
"name."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2948-9
msgid "Names starting with:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:2951-13
msgid "<b>0</b> - Executed very early and only once after an update"
msgstr "✅ MuPDF (Windows/Android)"

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:2952-13
msgid ""
"<b>1</b> - Excuted very early on every start of KOReader (but after 0 if "
"applicable)"
msgstr "⚠️ Zathura (if MuPDF plugin is enabled)"

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:2953-13
msgid ""
"<b>2</b> - Executed after <span class=\"ui\">UIManager</span> is ready on "
"every start of KOReader"
msgstr "❌ Adobe Acrobat Reader"

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:2954-13
msgid "<b>3-7</b> - Reserved"
msgstr "❌ Evince (Linux)"

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:2955-13
msgid "<b>8</b> - Executed before exit and before settings get saved"
msgstr "❌ Foxit Reader"

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:2956-13
msgid "<b>9</b> - Executed right before exit"
msgstr "❌ LibreOffice Draw (as editor)"

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2959-9
msgid ""
"If you have a problem with a user patch, you can revert to your previous "
"configuration by removing the patch file."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:2964-5
msgctxt "user_guide/en.html+html.body.div.div:2964-5"
msgid "TIPS"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:2967-9
msgid "Updating KOReader"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2968-9
msgid ""
"KOReader can update itself over Wi-Fi. You can trigger the check via this "
"menu item:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:2970-9
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/top_hamburger.svg\" "
"style=\"width:26px;\"> → Update → Check for update"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:2972-9
msgid "Automatic dimmer"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2973-9
msgid ""
"KOReader can dim your frontlight to preserve battery if your device is idle "
"for a while. You can turn on and adjust this feature via:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:2975-9
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/gear.svg\" style="
"\"width:26px;\"> → Screen → Automatic dimmer"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:2977-9
msgid "Line/word count of a page"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2978-9
msgid ""
"If you want to know how many lines or words are being shown on the current "
"page you can see it at:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:2980-9
msgctxt "user_guide/en.html+html.body.div.div.div:2980-9"
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/top_hamburger.svg\" "
"style=\"width:26px;\"> → Book information"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:2983-9
msgid "How can I add a password lock to KOReader?"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:2984-9
msgid ""
"We don't have a direct option for this in KOReader. But there is a "
"workaround to achieve this kind of lock screen functionality. You can set up "
"KOReader to keep the screensaver on the screen until you enter a chosen "
"gesture. To achieve this:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div.ol.li:2988-13
msgid ""
"Choose any gesture (including the complex ones with custom multiswipes) and "
"make it your <b>\"unlock\"</b> gesture by going to:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div.ol.li.div:2989-17
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/gear.svg\" style="
"\"width:26px;\"> → Taps and gestures → Gesture manager → "
"\"your selected gesture\" → Device → Exit screensaver"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div.ol.li:2991-13
msgid "And then enable this option:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div.ol.li.div:2992-17
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/gear.svg\" style="
"\"width:26px;\"> → Screen → Screensaver → Settings → Keep the screensaver on "
"screen after wakeup → Until 'Exit screensaver' gesture"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:2998-9
msgid "Switching between documents quickly"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:2999-9
msgid ""
"If you need to switch between two documents (when comparing them for example)"
", there is a quicker way than going through the <span class=\"ui\">File "
"Browser</span>. KOReader can open the last document with a gesture (<b>←→← "
"multiswipe</b>). If you define a gesture’s action as <span class=\"ui\">Open "
"previous document</span>, you can switch between two documents quickly "
"similar to <b>Alt+Tab</b> feature on the desktop computers. You can find "
"this feature under:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:3001-9
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/gear.svg\" style="
"\"width:26px;\"> → Taps and gestures → Gesture manager → “ANY GESTURE” → "
"General → Open Previous Document"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:3003-9
msgid ""
"Also you can use the <span class=\"ui\">History</span> dialog to switch "
"between documents quickly. The history screen can be opened with the <b>→↑</"
"b> multiswipe gesture. You can also define any other gesture for this of "
"course."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:3005-9
msgid "Applying current defaults to an already opened book"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:3006-9
msgid ""
"When you adjust your document defaults like <span class=\"ui\">default line "
"spacing</span> or <span class=\"ui\">default contrast</span>, this new value "
"will only be used for the new documents you open after the change. Your "
"already opened books will look the same. For example, if you change your "
"default <span class=\"ui\">FONT</span>, you will probably adjust <span class="
"\"ui\">FONT WEIGHT</span> and <span class=\"ui\">LINE SPACING</span> to more "
"suitable values for this new font. Then probably you will want to apply "
"these changes to all your opened books. With this feature you don’t need to "
"change these values manually in all your opened books."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:3007-9
msgid ""
"You can easily apply these changes to your already opened books by choosing:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:3009-9
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/top_document.svg\" "
"style=\"width:26px;\"> → Reset document settings to default"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:3011-9
msgid ""
"When you tap this option, your current book will reset to latest defaults "
"you set. Don’t worry, this will only change the appearance of the book. Your "
"reading position, highlights, notes and bookmarks will be preserved."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:3013-9
msgid "Saving current book settings as defaults"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:3014-9
msgid ""
"When you adjust a book to your liking, for example by changing <span class="
"\"ui\">line spacing</span>, <span class=\"ui\">font contrast</span> etc. you "
"can save all the changes at once as <span class=\"ui\">defaults</span>. Then "
"you can apply these settings to other books with the <span class=\"ui\""
">Reset document settings to default</span> option as explained above."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:3015-9
msgid ""
"You can save your changes as <span class=\"ui\">defaults</span> by choosing:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:3017-9
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/top_document.svg\" "
"style=\"width:26px;\"> → Save document settings as default"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:3019-9
msgid "Avoiding opening links accidentally"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:3020-9
msgid ""
"If your document has links and you are accidentally tapping them while "
"turning the page or using other gestures, you can turn off <span class=\"ui\""
">Following links by tapping</span> via this menu item:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:3022-9
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/gear.svg\" style="
"\"width:26px;\"> → Taps and Gestures → Links → Tap to follow links"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:3024-9
msgid ""
"After disabling this setting, to follow a link you have to long-tap on it "
"and select <span class=\"ui\">Follow link</span> from the popup menu. If you "
"have the opposite problem and you want to make tapping links easier, you can "
"enable <span class=\"ui\">Allow larger tap area around links</span> from the "
"same menu."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:3027-9
msgid "Optimizing your battery life"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:3029-9
msgid ""
"Li-ion batteries experience more degradation at the extreme ends of their "
"charge levels. To minimize this degradation and extend your battery life, "
"you can limit your minimum discharge level to <b>20%</b> and maximum charge "
"level to <b>80%</b> (as in electric vehicles and some newer phones). Which "
"means you start charging your device when the battery goes down to 20% and "
"unplug when it reaches 80% (or 25%-75% if you are extra cautious)."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:3031-9
msgid ""
"KOReader can warn you by showing an alert when charge level reaches your "
"defined limits:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:3033-9
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/gear.svg\" style="
"\"width:26px;\"> → Device Status Alerts → Battery Level"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:3036-9
msgid "Keeping an eye on your memory usage"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:3037-9
msgid ""
"In older Kindle devices some of our users reported crashes due to limited "
"memory. KOReader memory usage can go up if you open many files in one "
"session. Especially PDF’s increase this amount. You can add a memory "
"indicator to your <span class=\"ui\">STATUS BAR</span> and restart KOReader "
"if this value gets high, to avoid crashes or reboots."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:3039-9
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/gear.svg\" style="
"\"width:26px;\"> → Status Bar → KOReader memory usage"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:3041-9
msgid ""
"Also you can configure KOReader to restart automatically if memory usage "
"reaches a threshold via:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:3042-9
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/gear.svg\" style="
"\"width:26px;\"> → Device → Device Status Alerts"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:3045-9
msgid "Checking your battery consumption details"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:3046-9
msgid "You can see your detailed battery usage statistics via this menu item:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:3048-9
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/top_tools.svg\" style="
"\"width:26px;\"> → More Tools → Battery Statistics"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:3050-9
msgid "Checking detailed device statistics"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:3051-9
msgid ""
"You can see your system information like <b>CPU/DISK SPACE/RAM</b> usage via "
"this menu item:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:3053-9
msgctxt "user_guide/en.html+html.body.div.div.div:3053-9"
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/top_hamburger.svg\" "
"style=\"width:26px;\"> → Help → System statistics"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:3056-9
msgid "Changing your book cover"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:3057-9
msgid "You can change your book cover from this menu:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:3059-9
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/top_hamburger.svg\" "
"style=\"width:26px;\"> → Book information → <img class=\"img_inline\" src="
"\"pictures/top_hamburger.svg\" style=\"width:26px;\"> → Set cover image"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:3062-9
msgid "Reading statistics after midnight"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:3063-9
msgid ""
"In reading statistics you can change the start of day used for calculations. "
"This is useful if you are reading after midnight for example and want your "
"reading session counted as today instead of the next day. This applies only "
"to the <span class=\"ui\">Day timeline view</span> and optionally to the "
"<span class=\"ui\">Calendar view</span>; it does not apply to any of the "
"other statistics reports. You can set this time at:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:3065-9
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/top_tools.svg\" style="
"\"width:26px;\"> → Reading statistics → Settings → Daily timeline starts "
"at..."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:3072-5
msgctxt "user_guide/en.html+html.body.div.div:3072-5"
msgid "TROUBLESHOOTING"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:3076-5
msgid "If your book is slow"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:3078-5
msgid ""
"KOReader is optimized to work fast even on the limited hardware of e-book "
"readers. Generally thousand page books can be opened in seconds and page "
"turning is immediate. Here we will talk about the reasons if your book feels "
"very slow when opening, page turning or adjusting its appearance."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:3080-5
msgid "If the problematic book is a PDF:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:3082-9
msgid "PDF file itself might be <b>too big for your device memory</b>."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:3083-9
msgid ""
"PDF file <b>might contain very large image files</b>. Even in documents with "
"a normal text layer (which you can select and highlight) there might be "
"another image layer embedded (generally a scan of the page). This slows down "
"the opening and page turning because these large images has to be rescaled "
"to fit on your screen and this process can be CPU intensive."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:3084-9
msgid ""
"PDF file might have <b>lots of individual elements</b> that needs precise "
"positioning, like a magazine page with lots of images and text boxes. In "
"this case KOReader has to calculate and draw all these elements which can "
"take time."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:3085-9
msgid ""
"<span class=\"ui\">Auto straighten</span> feature (which allows you to "
"adjust the tilt of the page) might also slow down your reader."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:3086-9
msgid ""
"If you set your <span class=\"ui\">RENDER QUALITY</span> to <span class="
"\"ui\">HIGH</span> while <span class=\"ui\">REFLOW</span> is <b>ON</b>, text "
"will be more pleasing but it can be much slower (up to several seconds per "
"page turn) than <span class=\"ui\">DEFAULT</span> depending on your document."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li.div:3087-13
msgid ""
"⇓ BOTTOM MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src="
"\"pictures/bottom_contrast.svg\" style=\"width:26px;\"> → Render Quality"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:3092-5
msgid "If the problematic book is an EPUB:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:3095-9
msgid ""
"EPUB files are basically composed of text and images with some rules to "
"determine how these items are formatted on the screen. In ideal conditions, "
"this is a fairly simple process so EPUB files are generally fast in "
"KOReader. <b>But some EPUB books add a great number of formatting rules that "
"KOReader has to do many calculations just to show even a single sentence.</"
"b> This will slow down opening the book, turning the pages and changing the "
"appearance properties like font weight or line spacing."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li.div:3097-9
msgid ""
"<span class=\"label_blue\">INFO</span> KOReader doesn't support <b>fixed "
"layout EPUBs</b>. They will open, but will render as reflowable EPUBs and "
"probably won't look nice or readable."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:3100-9
msgid ""
"EPUB files are ZIP archives that contain HTML files. Some books can be a "
"single HTML file while others may be composed of multiple HTML files like "
"each chapter of the book is a separate HTML file. <b>If your book is only a "
"single HTML file, partial rendering can not work.</b> So appearance changes "
"will be slower than the divided chapter books, because for each change, "
"KOReader still has to calculate the whole book instead of only the current "
"chapter."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:3102-9
msgid ""
"Another rare case of slowness is when the content is wrapped in a <b>HTML "
"table tag</b>. KOReader has to render/draw each cell on each page turn, so "
"if a cell (containing many paragraphs) spans 50 pages, this will make page "
"turning quite slow. See below for the solution."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:3106-5
msgid "If everything is slow:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:3108-5
msgid ""
"Reasons mentioned above is generally valid if only some of your books are "
"slow. If all of your books are slow, your problem might be device related:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:3111-9
msgid "Very slow CPU or low RAM."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:3112-9
msgid ""
"Your flash memory (where your books reside) might be degrading, which is "
"generally due to the old age of the device."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:3113-9
msgid "You are running out of storage space."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:3114-9
msgid ""
"If you are using an Android based device, your Android OS might be "
"interfering with the operation of KOReader or some background processes "
"might be using your system resources."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:3118-5
msgid "SOLUTIONS:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:3120-5
msgid ""
"Unfortunately, for bad PDF files there are not many solutions. Generally "
"best solution with problematic PDFs and EPUBs is trying to find a better "
"version of it. Or if another file type is available for download, like EPUB "
"instead of PDF (or reverse) you can try that format."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:3122-5
msgid ""
"Following solutions are for EPUB files and they might require advanced "
"knowledge:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:3125-9
msgid ""
"You can set <span class=\"ui\">Embedded Styles</span> to <b>OFF</b> in the "
"bottom menu to see if ignoring all the document stylesheets makes it faster ("
"of course, you'll probably lose any nice formatting, but you'll know what is "
"the culprit)."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:3127-9
msgid ""
"If you have HTML and CSS knowledge, you can inspect the HTML and the CSS "
"files directly from KOReader and judge their quality or unnecessary "
"complexity by yourself. To do this, you can long-press on some text and "
"choose <span class=\"ui\">View HTML</span> in the popup menu."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:3129-9
msgid ""
"If you have the <b>“content wrapped in a table”</b> problem as mentioned "
"above in the problems section, you can add this <span class=\"ui\">table, "
"tr, td { display:block; }</span> book-specific style tweak to:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li.div:3131-9
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/top_document.svg\" "
"style=\"width:26px;\"> → Style tweaks → Book-specific tweak"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:3134-9
msgid ""
"<span class=\"external\">Calibre</span>’s e-book editor can check EPUB files "
"for problems and has tools to fix some of the problems."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li.p:3135-9
msgid ""
"You can download <span class=\"external\">Calibre</span> from here: <a href="
"\"https://calibre-ebook.com/\">https://calibre-ebook.com/</a>"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li.p:3137-9
msgid ""
"You can see the instructions for the <b>Check book tool</b> of <span class="
"\"external\">Calibre</span> here: <a href="
"\"https://manual.calibre-ebook.com/edit.html#checking-the-book\">https://"
"manual.calibre-ebook.com/edit.html#checking-the-book</a>"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:3139-9
msgid ""
"<span class=\"external\">EPUBCheck</span> application can check the validity "
"of the EPUB files and detect many types of errors. You can read an example "
"issue, where the problem is detected with <span class=\"external\""
">EPUBCheck</span> <a href="
"\"https://github.com/koreader/koreader/issues/11268\">https://github.com/"
"koreader/koreader/issues/11268</a>"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li.p:3141-9
msgid ""
"You can download the <b>command line version</b> from here: <a href="
"\"https://github.com/w3c/epubcheck\">https://github.com/w3c/epubcheck</a>"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li.p:3143-9
msgid ""
"Or download a <b>graphical user interface version</b> from here: <a href="
"\"https://github.com/w3c/epubcheck/wiki/GUI\">https://github.com/w3c/"
"epubcheck/wiki/GUI</a>"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:3147-5
msgid "Opening an issue:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:3148-5
msgid ""
"If you are opening an issue about this problem, it is important for us to "
"inspect the problematic file. You can share the file directly by dragging "
"and dropping it on your GitHub message after compressing it as a ZIP file. "
"If your book is an EPUB and you don’t want to share the file due to "
"copyright or privacy issues, there is a plugin for <span class=\"external\""
">Calibre</span> named <span class=\"external\">ScrambleEbook</span> which "
"you can access the download and instructions from this page:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:3148-500
msgid "https://www.mobileread.com/forums/showthread.php?t=267998"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:3151-5
msgid ""
"This plugin will read an un-DRM'd ebook file (EPUB/KEPUB/AZW3) and create a "
"copy of the book with <b>its text replaced with random characters</b>. You "
"can share this scrambled version with us in your issue thread. <b>Text of "
"the book will not be readable and there won’t be any copyright violation</b> "
"but we can still use this file for diagnostic purposes."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:3153-5
msgid ""
"Here you can see this procedure in a real issue involving a very problematic "
"EPUB file as an example:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div:3153-109
msgid "https://github.com/koreader/koreader/issues/11465"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:3160-5
msgid "My status bar disappeared"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:3161-9
msgid ""
"Probably you tapped on the <span class=\"ui\">STATUS BAR</span> touch zone "
"at the bottom of the screen. You can bring it back by tapping the same zone."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:3163-5
msgid "Sometimes my taps are registered as a long tap or double taps"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:3164-9
msgid ""
"This can happen in cases like shaking hands or device touch screen problems. "
"If you have this problem, you can try to increase the <span class=\"ui\">Tap "
"interval</span>. By increasing this interval, you tell KOReader to ignore "
"quick taps at the same location."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:3166-9
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/gear.svg\" style="
"\"width:26px;\"> → Taps and Gestures → Gesture intervals → Tap interval"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:3168-9
msgid ""
"If your two consecutive taps are separated by a distance, this would not "
"apply. So you can still quickly browse pages by tapping quickly "
"alternatively with two fingers."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:3170-5
msgid "KOReader can't write to the SD card"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:3171-9
msgid ""
"In Android devices KOReader can’t write to the external storage due to "
"Android system restrictions. If you want to change your screenshot saving "
"location, be careful to choose your device’s internal storage."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:3173-5
msgid "Ghosting and residue when turning pages"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:3174-9
msgid ""
"Even if KOReader is set to <b>full refresh after every page</b>, you may "
"still see some ghosting/residue after turning pages. This is a limitation of "
"e-ink screen technology and can be observed on the latest generation "
"devices, especially while reading mixed content (text+images) documents. As "
"a workaround, you can refresh one more time manually after turning the page "
"to get rid of these artifacts if they bother you (<span class=\"ui\">short "
"diagonal swipe</span> gesture by default)."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:3176-5
msgid "Sleep cover problems"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:3177-9
msgid ""
"Sleep covers generally use a magnet embedded in the cover which enables wake "
"up and sleep events via triggering a sensor in your device. In some cases "
"like misaligned magnets, weak magnets etc. this triggering can be "
"problematic. If you are having problems with waking up your device with your "
"cover, you can disable this feature via this menu:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:3179-9
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/gear.svg\" style="
"\"width:26px;\"> → Device → Ignore all sleep cover events"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:3181-5
msgid "Text indentation problems"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:3182-9
msgid ""
"If you get miscentered titles, headings or separators, or unexpected text "
"indentation, try switching the style for your document. <span class=\"ui\""
">epub.css</span> to <span class=\"ui\">html5.css</span>. This kind of "
"problems happen because some publishers assume their books will only be read "
"on <b>web browser engine based</b> readers, so they don't bother "
"\"resetting\" the styles."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:3184-9
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU → <img class=\"img_inline\" src=\"pictures/top_document.svg\" "
"style=\"width:24px;\"> → Style"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:3188-13
msgid ""
"Default <span class=\"ui\">HTML/EPUB (epub.css)</span> is our book-oriented "
"stylesheet, with <b>text-align: justify, text-indent on P</b>. It is better "
"for unstyled books, and might make styled books more readable."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.ul.li:3190-13
msgid ""
"You can try switching to <span class=\"ui\">HTML5 (html5.css)</span> if your "
"book has indentation problems as mentioned above. This style provides a base "
"stylesheet like web browsers do when rendering: <b>text-align: left, no text-"
"indent on P, spacing between P</b>. But it doesn’t look pretty when "
"publishers hasn’t done any styling."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:3194-5
msgid "Cleaning your book cover cache database"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:3195-9
msgid ""
"KOReader keeps a cache of your book covers to be able to show them quicker. "
"In normal conditions this cache doesn’t get too big. If you remove lots of "
"books or rename directories, you may want to clean up your book cover cache "
"database to reclaim some space. You can do it from this menu:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:3197-9
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU (in File Browser) → <img class=\"img_inline\" src="
"\"pictures/top_cabinet.svg\" style=\"width:26px;\"> → Settings → Mosaic and "
"detailed list settings → Book info cache management"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:3200-5
msgid "Clearing file cache"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:3201-9
msgid ""
"When you are reading a <b>PDF/DJVU</b> document, KOReader keeps a cache of "
"the last page you have read. So when you reopen the book, it will be faster. "
"But this cache can grow big if you are using KOReader for a long time and "
"reading many PDF/DJVU documents. These cache files are kept under your "
"KOReader installation directory under the <b>cache folder</b>. To clear this "
"cache and reclaim the space you can go to:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:3203-9
msgid ""
"⇑ TOP MENU (in file browser) → <img class=\"img_inline\" src="
"\"pictures/top_tools.svg\" style=\"width:26px;\"> → More tools → Developer "
"options → Clear caches"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:3205-9
msgid ""
"<span class=\"label_red\">WARNING</span> Clear this cache <b>only if you "
"really need this space</b>. If you have enough space, clearing the cache "
"will not provide any benefit. Instead, it will degrade the performance "
"because your reader will have to render those pages again."
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div:3208-5
msgid "Backing up your KOReader settings"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.p:3209-9
msgid ""
"In rare cases that you want to backup and restore your KOReader with all "
"your settings, you can backup these folders and files under the KOReader "
"installation directory. Then you can overwrite them after a clean "
"installation to restore your settings:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div.div:3212-13
msgid "Folders:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div.div.ul.li:3215-13
msgid "settings"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div.div.ul.li:3216-13
msgid "styletweaks"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div.div:3220-13
msgid "Files:"
msgstr ""

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.div.div.div.ul.li:3223-21
msgid "data/cr3.ini"
msgstr ""

